1
00:00:00,547 --> 00:00:02,077
(2 guests visit 2 Days 1 Night.)

2
00:00:02,247 --> 00:00:03,477
(Born entertainer Boom)

3
00:00:03,677 --> 00:00:06,187
(Rising star Kim Jae Won)

4
00:00:06,618 --> 00:00:08,417
(The winter workshop of 2 Days 1 Night)

5
00:00:08,418 --> 00:00:09,858
- The winter workshop?
- The winter workshop?

6
00:00:10,358 --> 00:00:13,158
(You can't have a workshop without games.)

7
00:00:14,388 --> 00:00:16,358
(Rolling down the snow is a must on TV shows.)

8
00:00:16,528 --> 00:00:17,598
- Three, four.
- Three, four.

9
00:00:18,228 --> 00:00:19,498
(Happily celebrating together)

10
00:00:20,028 --> 00:00:21,298
(Superstars are closers.)

11
00:00:22,198 --> 00:00:23,598
- Okay.
- Come on.

12
00:00:23,868 --> 00:00:26,208
(We expected too much from him.)

13
00:00:26,408 --> 00:00:27,937
(And there was some delicious food.)

14
00:00:27,938 --> 00:00:29,838
(Happy)

15
00:00:30,578 --> 00:00:34,178
(The winter workshop is more fun with the guests.)

16
00:00:35,448 --> 00:00:36,547
(They thought...)

17
00:00:36,548 --> 00:00:38,848
(the workshop couldn't be any better.)

18
00:00:39,178 --> 00:00:40,548
(Let's get off the bus now.)

19
00:00:41,648 --> 00:00:44,888
(The sudden drop-off made the members nervous.)

20
00:00:46,058 --> 00:00:48,728
(They had to switch vehicles to continue the journey?)

21
00:00:49,088 --> 00:00:50,228
(I have a bad feeling about this.)

22
00:00:50,698 --> 00:00:51,998
(Something doesn't feel right.)

23
00:00:52,228 --> 00:00:54,528
(Why can't the bus go there?)

24
00:00:54,728 --> 00:00:57,168
(Their gut told them they were heading someplace rough.)

25
00:00:57,368 --> 00:00:58,768
We are going into the mountains.

26
00:00:59,098 --> 00:01:01,268
(Where on earth are they going?)

27
00:01:02,468 --> 00:01:06,208
(2 Days 1 Night)

28
00:01:06,678 --> 00:01:08,278
We're going up the mountains.

29
00:01:09,378 --> 00:01:10,918
We're going up there.

30
00:01:11,278 --> 00:01:12,988
Gosh, we're going deep into the mountains.

31
00:01:13,318 --> 00:01:15,017
- Yes, this can't be good.
- Se Yoon.

32
00:01:15,018 --> 00:01:16,718
- Yes?
- We're going deep in there.

33
00:01:17,158 --> 00:01:19,018
My heart is pounding. Let me stay quiet for a second.

34
00:01:19,528 --> 00:01:21,788
I don't see any marks on the GPS now.

35
00:01:23,158 --> 00:01:25,197
This is the only path. We're in trouble.

36
00:01:25,198 --> 00:01:26,298
(Nothing's around this path.)

37
00:01:27,168 --> 00:01:29,897
(They drive into the barren mountains to no end.)

38
00:01:29,898 --> 00:01:31,838
- I don't see any houses.
- I only see rice paddies.

39
00:01:32,038 --> 00:01:33,268
Right, they're all rice paddies.

40
00:01:33,538 --> 00:01:35,308
If we were to do the winter training,

41
00:01:35,608 --> 00:01:37,437
we would have to build our own house?

42
00:01:37,438 --> 00:01:39,477
- We slept under boxes last year.
- Really?

43
00:01:39,478 --> 00:01:41,448
We have guests today. We shouldn't do the winter training.

44
00:01:41,848 --> 00:01:43,218
That will be too cruel on the guests.

45
00:01:43,448 --> 00:01:44,917
That can't be it.

46
00:01:44,918 --> 00:01:45,918
(Yes, DinDin has to be right.)

47
00:01:45,919 --> 00:01:47,148
- It can't be winter training.
- Did he say we'd do it?

48
00:01:48,318 --> 00:01:51,087
(Is DinDin right about this?)

49
00:01:51,088 --> 00:01:52,728
- I think we're here.
- What?

50
00:01:52,958 --> 00:01:54,788
- Isn't that a house?
- It's a house.

51
00:01:55,328 --> 00:01:56,457
There's a house.

52
00:01:56,458 --> 00:01:58,128
- That's not it?
- It's not.

53
00:01:58,428 --> 00:02:00,198
- We're driving past it.
- We're driving past it.

54
00:02:00,498 --> 00:02:02,198
This is the perfect spot for winter training.

55
00:02:02,298 --> 00:02:03,938
- My gosh.
- It's the winter training.

56
00:02:04,398 --> 00:02:05,937
(Past the house...)

57
00:02:05,938 --> 00:02:06,968
There's nothing here.

58
00:02:07,308 --> 00:02:09,508
We'll do winter training with the guests?

59
00:02:10,008 --> 00:02:11,107
(As it's at the foot of the mountain,)

60
00:02:11,108 --> 00:02:14,548
(it's shaded.)

61
00:02:14,908 --> 00:02:16,848
(The stream has frozen.)

62
00:02:17,478 --> 00:02:19,118
Gosh, it's completely frozen.

63
00:02:20,648 --> 00:02:23,558
(Is this barren spot for the winter training?)

64
00:02:23,988 --> 00:02:26,018
- Are we doing the winter training?
- I think we are.

65
00:02:26,188 --> 00:02:27,287
I think we'll sleep there.

66
00:02:27,288 --> 00:02:28,558
(The experienced member's gut says it is.)

67
00:02:29,528 --> 00:02:32,198
(I don't want to believe this is real.)

68
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:34,728
What's going on?

69
00:02:35,328 --> 00:02:36,738
- What's this?
- Is this our destination?

70
00:02:37,268 --> 00:02:38,798
- Yes.
- What?

71
00:02:39,068 --> 00:02:40,307
Let's get out a little later.

72
00:02:40,308 --> 00:02:41,808
Jong Min won't get out either.

73
00:02:42,338 --> 00:02:43,937
- You guys will wait.
- We'll wait.

74
00:02:43,938 --> 00:02:45,407
(You'll wait for the other team.)

75
00:02:45,408 --> 00:02:47,278
We'll get out once the other team gets out.

76
00:02:47,678 --> 00:02:48,878
- Gosh, this is...
- What?

77
00:02:50,018 --> 00:02:51,978
- Yes.
- Please get out of the car.

78
00:02:52,178 --> 00:02:53,987
- We have to get out?
- Yes.

79
00:02:53,988 --> 00:02:56,318
(He refuses to get out by using Jong Min's impression.)

80
00:02:56,518 --> 00:02:57,718
They want us to get out.

81
00:02:59,388 --> 00:03:00,857
Once you get out, you can't get back in.

82
00:03:00,858 --> 00:03:02,927
Wait. Has anyone filmed in a place like this before?

83
00:03:02,928 --> 00:03:05,357
(Team Boom gets out first.)

84
00:03:05,358 --> 00:03:06,331
What are we doing here?

85
00:03:06,498 --> 00:03:08,028
Hey.

86
00:03:09,798 --> 00:03:11,097
- Get out already.
- You already stepped out?

87
00:03:11,098 --> 00:03:12,168
They told us to get out.

88
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:15,068
I didn't know things would be this bad.

89
00:03:15,268 --> 00:03:16,308
Hey.

90
00:03:16,638 --> 00:03:18,408
- Take your speaker.
- Leave it there.

91
00:03:18,508 --> 00:03:21,007
You won't be able to see this vehicle again.

92
00:03:21,008 --> 00:03:22,848
- Really?
- I have a bad feeling about this.

93
00:03:23,248 --> 00:03:24,577
(Both teams get out after long deliberation.)

94
00:03:24,578 --> 00:03:26,018
- We really have to get out here?
- Yes.

95
00:03:26,288 --> 00:03:28,548
(Looking slightly terrified)

96
00:03:28,748 --> 00:03:29,757
The ground is frozen.

97
00:03:29,758 --> 00:03:31,588
I can't even walk on it because it's frozen.

98
00:03:31,958 --> 00:03:34,658
Everyone, this is...

99
00:03:35,258 --> 00:03:36,597
your final destination today.

100
00:03:36,598 --> 00:03:38,398
(The final destination of today's trip)

101
00:03:39,728 --> 00:03:41,698
(Shocked)

102
00:03:42,028 --> 00:03:44,137
- The final destination?
- Where on earth are we?

103
00:03:44,138 --> 00:03:45,738
- The final destination...
- All right.

104
00:03:46,098 --> 00:03:47,407
- What?
- The house...

105
00:03:47,408 --> 00:03:49,138
- Something is coming. What's that?
- It's a field.

106
00:03:49,308 --> 00:03:50,837
- What's this?
- What is it?

107
00:03:50,838 --> 00:03:52,338
- It's going to explode.
- What's that?

108
00:03:52,608 --> 00:03:53,677
- What is it?
- Be careful.

109
00:03:53,678 --> 00:03:55,677
- It's going to explode.
- What's that?

110
00:03:55,678 --> 00:03:56,778
Be careful.

111
00:03:57,248 --> 00:03:58,478
What is it? It's a message.

112
00:03:59,118 --> 00:04:00,388
No. It's a bomb.

113
00:04:01,088 --> 00:04:02,218
- Dodge it.
- What is it?

114
00:04:02,518 --> 00:04:04,588
- What?
- No way. Did it drop that?

115
00:04:05,418 --> 00:04:07,488
(Falling)

116
00:04:07,828 --> 00:04:09,258
- What is it?
- Why are we doing this?

117
00:04:09,528 --> 00:04:10,998
They could've handed it to us. Why...

118
00:04:12,198 --> 00:04:14,027
- What a fun show.
- What on earth was that?

119
00:04:14,028 --> 00:04:15,028
(Bye)

120
00:04:15,528 --> 00:04:18,468
(They open it right away.)

121
00:04:19,808 --> 00:04:20,868
- What is it?
- It's an invitation.

122
00:04:21,768 --> 00:04:23,638
- What is it?
- It's an invitation.

123
00:04:24,578 --> 00:04:26,137
- An invitation. One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

124
00:04:26,138 --> 00:04:27,207
"We invite you..." See?

125
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:28,848
(Come on!)

126
00:04:29,148 --> 00:04:30,317
"You have entered the Real Winter Training Center."

127
00:04:30,318 --> 00:04:31,548
- "Welcome."
- Seriously?

128
00:04:32,548 --> 00:04:35,487
(It's an invitation to the winter training.)

129
00:04:35,488 --> 00:04:36,588
What? "Reboot?"

130
00:04:36,988 --> 00:04:38,387
My gosh. Things have changed on the show.

131
00:04:38,388 --> 00:04:40,227
Things have gotten tougher on 2 Days 1 Night.

132
00:04:40,228 --> 00:04:42,228
(I can't believe this.)

133
00:04:42,428 --> 00:04:44,798
The mandatory event of our show...

134
00:04:45,028 --> 00:04:47,198
has come back in 2026 without fail.

135
00:04:48,298 --> 00:04:50,338
We've prepared the Winter Training Special.

136
00:04:51,398 --> 00:04:53,068
We're doing this when we have guests today?

137
00:04:53,608 --> 00:04:55,268
What have the guests done wrong?

138
00:04:55,768 --> 00:04:56,877
It doesn't matter for us.

139
00:04:56,878 --> 00:04:58,637
- But...
- What's this?

140
00:04:58,638 --> 00:05:00,577
(Their concern turns into the reality.)

141
00:05:00,578 --> 00:05:03,318
Actually, we had already planned...

142
00:05:03,518 --> 00:05:05,378
- the Winter Training Special.
- Okay.

143
00:05:05,648 --> 00:05:10,157
Then the guests were available for the Winter Training Special.

144
00:05:10,158 --> 00:05:12,457
Had we known about this, we would've delayed our appearance.

145
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:13,458
- I see.
- Okay.

146
00:05:13,459 --> 00:05:15,588
I have a question. What about the house?

147
00:05:16,188 --> 00:05:17,005
- We...
- It's right here.

148
00:05:17,358 --> 00:05:18,797
- Where will we sleep?
- Right here.

149
00:05:18,798 --> 00:05:20,597
- Come on.
- It's right here.

150
00:05:20,598 --> 00:05:21,668
(It's right here.)

151
00:05:22,298 --> 00:05:23,367
(Boom explodes.)

152
00:05:23,368 --> 00:05:24,498
There's nothing here.

153
00:05:24,938 --> 00:05:26,198
Starting now,

154
00:05:26,938 --> 00:05:28,608
we have to figure out a way to survive.

155
00:05:29,108 --> 00:05:30,607
- It's about our survival now.
- Really?

156
00:05:30,608 --> 00:05:32,238
- It's all about our survival.
- Now...

157
00:05:32,271 --> 00:05:35,211
Before we begin the winter training,

158
00:05:35,608 --> 00:05:36,977
the members and the guests...

159
00:05:36,978 --> 00:05:38,378
- take a moment to stay strong.
- What?

160
00:05:38,818 --> 00:05:41,287
Let's continue with the Winter Training Oath.

161
00:05:41,288 --> 00:05:42,317
- Gosh, what's this?
- My gosh.

162
00:05:42,318 --> 00:05:44,417
- They want to silence us with it.
- All right.

163
00:05:44,418 --> 00:05:46,288
- That's right.
- We can't proceed with the oath!

164
00:05:46,858 --> 00:05:48,858
- The moment we do it, it's over.
- This is the invitation.

165
00:05:49,258 --> 00:05:50,998
- He ripped it.
- That's good.

166
00:05:51,198 --> 00:05:52,597
- Great.
- I'm sorry about this, Jae Won.

167
00:05:52,598 --> 00:05:53,598
No, it's okay.

168
00:05:53,599 --> 00:05:55,228
- No wonder why I'm so bad-tempered.
- Since we're here...

169
00:05:55,528 --> 00:05:57,597
- Right.
- No wonder why I'm so bad-tempered.

170
00:05:57,598 --> 00:05:58,998
- The thoughtful celebrity.
- Thought Celebrity DinDin.

171
00:05:59,568 --> 00:06:00,767
- His true colors are showing.
- Yes.

172
00:06:00,768 --> 00:06:01,907
No wonder...

173
00:06:01,908 --> 00:06:03,307
- His true colors are showing.
- Oh, no. They're going to come out.

174
00:06:03,308 --> 00:06:05,607
They're going to come out!

175
00:06:05,608 --> 00:06:06,707
- Bark.
- Woof.

176
00:06:06,708 --> 00:06:08,647
- Go ahead and bark.
- I can never be good-natured.

177
00:06:08,648 --> 00:06:09,917
- DinDin.
- You should've fed us lunch...

178
00:06:09,918 --> 00:06:11,377
before the winter training.

179
00:06:11,378 --> 00:06:12,647
I'm starving right now.

180
00:06:12,648 --> 00:06:14,387
What did you eat?

181
00:06:14,388 --> 00:06:16,458
What did I eat? I had to dig up potatoes.

182
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:18,488
Did you see how he moved his fist?

183
00:06:18,888 --> 00:06:21,788
(It's understandable that he's sensitive since he's hungry.)

184
00:06:22,028 --> 00:06:24,258
From now on, we have to be sharp and objective.

185
00:06:25,228 --> 00:06:27,168
- That will be more efficient.
- So we should cave in?

186
00:06:27,268 --> 00:06:28,668
- So you want to build a house now?
- Right.

187
00:06:29,328 --> 00:06:30,668
- While the sun is still out.
- My gosh.

188
00:06:30,998 --> 00:06:32,367
- Here we go.
- Go where?

189
00:06:32,368 --> 00:06:33,368
(We'll swear an oath.)

190
00:06:33,968 --> 00:06:35,067
"Oath."

191
00:06:35,068 --> 00:06:36,167
- No.
- "Oath."

192
00:06:36,168 --> 00:06:37,577
(He refuses to take an oath.)

193
00:06:37,578 --> 00:06:39,237
- No.
- That's not how you do it?

194
00:06:39,238 --> 00:06:40,248
No.

195
00:06:40,848 --> 00:06:42,408
Don't waste time. The sun is going down.

196
00:06:43,318 --> 00:06:44,477
It's more painful when the sun goes down. Seriously.

197
00:06:44,478 --> 00:06:45,977
- It's behind you.
- It is. We must hurry up.

198
00:06:45,978 --> 00:06:47,247
Raise your hand when he starts.

199
00:06:47,248 --> 00:06:48,887
Here we go. One, two, three.

200
00:06:48,888 --> 00:06:49,987
"Oath."

201
00:06:49,988 --> 00:06:51,158
- "Oath."
- "Oath."

202
00:06:51,758 --> 00:06:53,288
- One.
- One.

203
00:06:53,828 --> 00:06:57,258
"We may be dealing with a harsh wilderness at minus 15°C,"

204
00:06:57,758 --> 00:07:00,767
"but we swear not to spare our body and mind..."

205
00:07:00,768 --> 00:07:03,138
"to deliver raw, unfiltered moments of entertainment to the viewers."

206
00:07:03,438 --> 00:07:04,897
- We swear.
- We swear.

207
00:07:04,898 --> 00:07:05,938
We swear.

208
00:07:06,238 --> 00:07:07,708
- "Two."
- "Two."

209
00:07:08,108 --> 00:07:10,438
"To continue the spirit of the real wild variety show,"

210
00:07:11,078 --> 00:07:13,248
"we won't sulk or get upset."

211
00:07:13,508 --> 00:07:15,377
"We swear to do our best..."

212
00:07:15,378 --> 00:07:18,148
"with our fellow members while keeping a positive mindset."

213
00:07:18,648 --> 00:07:20,818
"I, Kim Jong Min, swear on behalf of 2 Days 1 Night."

214
00:07:21,218 --> 00:07:22,348
"and on behalf of the guests..."

215
00:07:24,088 --> 00:07:25,118
Boom.

216
00:07:25,388 --> 00:07:27,027
- Kim Jae Won.
- Okay.

217
00:07:27,028 --> 00:07:28,257
(Jae Won also takes an oath.)

218
00:07:28,258 --> 00:07:29,428
- That's it.
- At ease.

219
00:07:29,558 --> 00:07:30,597
- At ease.
- At ease.

220
00:07:30,598 --> 00:07:31,658
This is bad.

221
00:07:32,058 --> 00:07:33,098
- All right.
- This is...

222
00:07:34,468 --> 00:07:36,798
(Dead of Winter: The coldest period of the year)

223
00:07:37,368 --> 00:07:40,238
(It's cold enough for the flowing water to freeze up.)

224
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:43,038
(They must overcome the extreme cold.)

225
00:07:44,178 --> 00:07:46,337
(The dead of winter is back!)

226
00:07:46,338 --> 00:07:49,378
(Entertain the viewers even more in the dead of winter!)

227
00:07:49,848 --> 00:07:52,218
(Today's temperature is minus 15°C.)

228
00:07:52,918 --> 00:07:54,888
(Boom and Jae Won have joined today's episode as special guests.)

229
00:07:55,318 --> 00:07:57,388
(Special Winter Training)

230
00:07:57,688 --> 00:07:59,187
(Jumping hard)

231
00:07:59,188 --> 00:08:00,658
(This is Jae Won.)

232
00:08:01,588 --> 00:08:02,658
What is this?

233
00:08:02,958 --> 00:08:05,098
(Falling down hard)

234
00:08:06,258 --> 00:08:08,297
(Slouching)

235
00:08:08,298 --> 00:08:10,298
(This is Jae Won.)

236
00:08:10,668 --> 00:08:11,668
This is crazy.

237
00:08:11,669 --> 00:08:14,468
(What kind of trip will unfold for them?)

238
00:08:14,568 --> 00:08:17,238
First of all, we'll show you what we've prepared.

239
00:08:17,438 --> 00:08:18,678
- You've prepared something?
- You got something?

240
00:08:18,838 --> 00:08:19,978
What is this?

241
00:08:20,578 --> 00:08:23,147
They're giving us the merchandise. Here they come.

242
00:08:23,148 --> 00:08:24,577
- What are they?
- Merchandise for winter training.

243
00:08:24,578 --> 00:08:25,717
- Padded jackets.
- My gosh.

244
00:08:25,718 --> 00:08:26,788
- That's really nice.
- Oh, this.

245
00:08:27,648 --> 00:08:29,388
I can't believe I'm seeing this in person.

246
00:08:30,418 --> 00:08:31,587
The moment you put them on...

247
00:08:31,588 --> 00:08:32,588
(A jumper and a hat for the wilderness)

248
00:08:32,589 --> 00:08:34,188
- Whose hat is that?
- That's mine.

249
00:08:35,858 --> 00:08:38,197
Hold on. They gave nicer ones to the guests.

250
00:08:38,198 --> 00:08:39,198
What?

251
00:08:39,199 --> 00:08:41,867
He could wear the hat even after the show.

252
00:08:41,868 --> 00:08:42,928
It looks great on him.

253
00:08:43,598 --> 00:08:45,667
- That one looks fancy.
- It looks good on him.

254
00:08:45,668 --> 00:08:46,767
- Let me see. Wait.
- Yes.

255
00:08:46,768 --> 00:08:48,367
It looks like they're on different shows. Look.

256
00:08:48,368 --> 00:08:49,707
(It looks like they're on different shows.)

257
00:08:49,708 --> 00:08:51,207
You can't possibly think they're on the same show.

258
00:08:51,208 --> 00:08:52,808
His hat looks great. But what's wrong with yours?

259
00:08:53,078 --> 00:08:55,208
What? Do you think you look any better?

260
00:08:56,548 --> 00:08:58,178
The hat looks like a bump on your head.

261
00:08:58,978 --> 00:09:00,288
- One more thing.
- Yes.

262
00:09:00,588 --> 00:09:03,658
As for your personal belongings and your cell phone,

263
00:09:04,018 --> 00:09:06,488
- What?
- we'll keep them for you...

264
00:09:06,858 --> 00:09:09,228
until we finish filming tomorrow.

265
00:09:09,558 --> 00:09:11,697
(The two of them get speechless several times today.)

266
00:09:11,698 --> 00:09:13,968
- The world has changed a lot now.
- They're for real.

267
00:09:14,128 --> 00:09:15,997
Make your last call...

268
00:09:15,998 --> 00:09:17,737
and then turn in your phone.

269
00:09:17,738 --> 00:09:19,168
I'll give you five minutes.

270
00:09:20,168 --> 00:09:21,207
(A segment within a segment)

271
00:09:21,208 --> 00:09:22,638
(How will the last call for the husbands go?)

272
00:09:24,308 --> 00:09:26,448
They're taking away my phone for the winter training.

273
00:09:27,008 --> 00:09:28,277
Say hello to Director Joo.

274
00:09:28,278 --> 00:09:30,448
He's going to take everything now.

275
00:09:30,918 --> 00:09:33,288
Go easy on them. It's really cold today.

276
00:09:34,718 --> 00:09:35,718
Okay.

277
00:09:35,848 --> 00:09:37,218
Don't curse him out at the end.

278
00:09:38,158 --> 00:09:39,787
The microphone can pick up everything.

279
00:09:39,788 --> 00:09:41,327
What are you having for dinner? Okay.

280
00:09:41,328 --> 00:09:42,458
(The couple of 17 years is playful like friends.)

281
00:09:42,758 --> 00:09:46,158
It looks like something's going on with Jong Min.

282
00:09:46,568 --> 00:09:47,968
I think he's getting scolded now.

283
00:09:49,228 --> 00:09:51,468
They're taking away my phone for the winter training.

284
00:09:51,598 --> 00:09:52,768
I'll get it back tomorrow morning.

285
00:09:52,998 --> 00:09:54,838
Okay. Make sure to eat.

286
00:09:55,768 --> 00:09:56,838
Me too.

287
00:09:58,378 --> 00:09:59,707
(The newlyweds are full of love.)

288
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:00,708
Okay.

289
00:10:01,508 --> 00:10:03,348
Hello. Honey.

290
00:10:03,878 --> 00:10:06,048
What is it? What's wrong with your stomach?

291
00:10:06,097 --> 00:10:06,870
What?

292
00:10:07,494 --> 00:10:09,654
I see. Okay.

293
00:10:09,748 --> 00:10:10,451
It's cold.

294
00:10:10,711 --> 00:10:12,388
Your stomach...

295
00:10:13,428 --> 00:10:14,758
is very warm?

296
00:10:17,028 --> 00:10:19,198
(Why is he suddenly lowering his cell phone?)

297
00:10:19,698 --> 00:10:22,298
(He tries to escape by pretending to make a call.)

298
00:10:24,092 --> 00:10:25,198
I could get an electric shock.

299
00:10:26,938 --> 00:10:29,267
(It really says "electric shock.")

300
00:10:29,268 --> 00:10:30,807
- Se Yoon, we're in trouble.
- What?

301
00:10:30,808 --> 00:10:32,138
- This is bad.
- What do you mean?

302
00:10:32,238 --> 00:10:34,348
I checked out the fence to climb over.

303
00:10:34,548 --> 00:10:36,507
We're surrounded by electric barbed wires.

304
00:10:36,508 --> 00:10:38,418
- It says "electric shock."
- Where?

305
00:10:38,648 --> 00:10:40,017
- We're surrounded.
- Are you for real?

306
00:10:40,018 --> 00:10:42,017
(You can't escape.)

307
00:10:42,018 --> 00:10:43,757
- Right. Once we start, - Yes.

308
00:10:43,758 --> 00:10:45,617
- we'll make a house and play games.
- Right.

309
00:10:45,618 --> 00:10:47,128
We need materials to build a house with.

310
00:10:47,758 --> 00:10:49,657
- They will give us some stuff.
- Really? They will?

311
00:10:49,658 --> 00:10:51,228
Like wood and boxes.

312
00:10:53,698 --> 00:10:55,298
A long time ago, when we had the winter training,

313
00:10:55,368 --> 00:10:56,968
we had to dig the ground and sleep underground.

314
00:10:57,398 --> 00:10:58,698
- For real?
- Yes.

315
00:11:00,108 --> 00:11:04,308
(His story about sleeping underground was true.)

316
00:11:04,978 --> 00:11:06,277
That's crazy.

317
00:11:06,278 --> 00:11:07,547
(It almost sounds like an old folktale.)

318
00:11:07,548 --> 00:11:09,477
- This is really happening.
- Yes.

319
00:11:09,478 --> 00:11:10,677
We had to dig up the ground.

320
00:11:10,678 --> 00:11:12,618
But looking at the weather, I don't think we'll die.

321
00:11:12,848 --> 00:11:14,018
(Laughing in disbelief)

322
00:11:14,188 --> 00:11:16,758
(He's worried about his first winter training.)

323
00:11:16,918 --> 00:11:18,287
All right. What do we need to do?

324
00:11:18,288 --> 00:11:20,527
You'll need survival items...

325
00:11:20,528 --> 00:11:22,927
to overcome the winter training.

326
00:11:22,928 --> 00:11:23,928
Of course.

327
00:11:23,929 --> 00:11:25,897
- It's cold. So we need a house.
- We need a house.

328
00:11:25,898 --> 00:11:27,727
- We need sleeping bags...
- We really need that.

329
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:29,797
- and blankets to use in the house.
- Blankets.

330
00:11:29,798 --> 00:11:31,598
- Yes, blankets.
- We must have blankets.

331
00:11:31,798 --> 00:11:33,837
Food isn't that important today.

332
00:11:33,838 --> 00:11:35,367
It's quite cold today.

333
00:11:35,368 --> 00:11:38,177
We got the sleeping bags that are built to survive...

334
00:11:38,178 --> 00:11:39,977
the brutal cold of minus 40°C.

335
00:11:39,978 --> 00:11:42,447
So they probably didn't sleep well in the sleeping bags...

336
00:11:42,448 --> 00:11:44,318
at minus 40°C. They just survived, right?

337
00:11:44,978 --> 00:11:46,718
So they just survived.

338
00:11:46,818 --> 00:11:48,747
We can't sleep in it. We can probably survive the night.

339
00:11:48,748 --> 00:11:50,057
The director is...

340
00:11:50,058 --> 00:11:51,957
- toying with our heart.
- Yes.

341
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:52,958
Guys.

342
00:11:52,959 --> 00:11:54,858
- Do you see the truck over there?
- Yes.

343
00:11:55,028 --> 00:11:57,558
- The truck with props.
- The truck on the right...

344
00:11:58,228 --> 00:11:59,797
has everything anyone would need.

345
00:11:59,798 --> 00:12:01,027
It's the truck for our props.

346
00:12:01,028 --> 00:12:02,097
- Okay.
- For the props?

347
00:12:02,098 --> 00:12:03,998
You'll find materials you'd need to build a base camp.

348
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:07,338
There are also tools, the Warmth Set, fire making tools,

349
00:12:07,608 --> 00:12:10,738
cooking utensils, and other daily necessities.

350
00:12:10,978 --> 00:12:12,137
- In the truck?
- Okay.

351
00:12:12,138 --> 00:12:14,277
We'll give you a chance...

352
00:12:14,278 --> 00:12:16,407
to freely use the items on the truck.

353
00:12:16,408 --> 00:12:17,417
Really?

354
00:12:17,418 --> 00:12:19,677
When we open up the truck shortly,

355
00:12:19,678 --> 00:12:22,617
the four of you can freely grab materials you'd need...

356
00:12:22,618 --> 00:12:24,587
- to build a base camp.
- The four of us?

357
00:12:24,588 --> 00:12:26,857
However, the remaining three members...

358
00:12:26,858 --> 00:12:29,227
- will jump rope as a group.
- My gosh.

359
00:12:29,228 --> 00:12:32,558
Your mission will be over the moment anyone steps on the rope.

360
00:12:32,798 --> 00:12:34,327
- That's the worst.
- That's an important task.

361
00:12:34,328 --> 00:12:37,397
You'll have to spend the night with the items...

362
00:12:37,398 --> 00:12:38,698
you grab from the truck.

363
00:12:38,998 --> 00:12:40,107
My gosh. This is crazy.

364
00:12:40,108 --> 00:12:42,337
What if we step on the rope as soon as we begin?

365
00:12:42,338 --> 00:12:43,537
- It's over then.
- We need water.

366
00:12:43,538 --> 00:12:44,538
We'll sleep like this?

367
00:12:44,539 --> 00:12:47,478
I'm wearing seven layers of clothing.

368
00:12:47,678 --> 00:12:49,147
I can't move right now.

369
00:12:49,148 --> 00:12:51,118
I'm like a stuffed doll.

370
00:12:51,218 --> 00:12:52,847
It won't be easy to jump rope...

371
00:12:52,848 --> 00:12:54,288
- It won't be easy.
- on this ground.

372
00:12:54,488 --> 00:12:56,087
We're at a disadvantage.

373
00:12:56,088 --> 00:12:57,417
- Boom.
- What?

374
00:12:57,418 --> 00:12:59,117
Let me play the devil's advocate.

375
00:12:59,118 --> 00:13:01,057
- That brings back old memories.
- We can keep taking items...

376
00:13:01,058 --> 00:13:02,987
as long as we continue to jump rope. Right?

377
00:13:02,988 --> 00:13:03,998
That's right.

378
00:13:04,528 --> 00:13:05,797
- That brings back old memories.
- Right?

379
00:13:05,798 --> 00:13:06,827
- That's right, Ho Dong.
- Right?

380
00:13:06,828 --> 00:13:07,828
- Yes.
- Okay.

381
00:13:07,829 --> 00:13:09,768
The viewers can't feel that it's minus 10°C now.

382
00:13:10,398 --> 00:13:11,697
- Are you good at jump rope?
- My gosh.

383
00:13:11,698 --> 00:13:13,137
I think I'm pretty good at jumping.

384
00:13:13,138 --> 00:13:14,868
- No. Jae Won shouldn't do it.
- Okay.

385
00:13:15,538 --> 00:13:16,907
- It's okay, Jae Won.
- He's confident in everything.

386
00:13:16,908 --> 00:13:19,238
You can try it out later on your own.

387
00:13:19,508 --> 00:13:21,647
- Try it later.
- We're all bundled up now.

388
00:13:21,648 --> 00:13:22,947
It will be difficult.

389
00:13:22,948 --> 00:13:24,417
Jae Won, what are you good at? Be honest.

390
00:13:24,418 --> 00:13:25,777
- This is...
- That or jump rope?

391
00:13:25,778 --> 00:13:26,987
- But...
- If you lie, we won't be happy.

392
00:13:26,988 --> 00:13:29,817
as for food, we can try to cope with being hungry.

393
00:13:29,818 --> 00:13:31,257
- But this is about our survival.
- Right.

394
00:13:31,258 --> 00:13:32,887
- Are you good at jump rope?
- I'll switch if I can't do it.

395
00:13:32,888 --> 00:13:34,027
- So jump rope?
- Are you good at it?

396
00:13:34,028 --> 00:13:35,458
- Answer already!
- I like it.

397
00:13:36,128 --> 00:13:37,757
- What's wrong with you?
- Okay.

398
00:13:37,758 --> 00:13:39,997
- Right. Yes.
- The viewers...

399
00:13:39,998 --> 00:13:42,768
No. I'm getting frustrated since we're on the same team now.

400
00:13:43,028 --> 00:13:44,837
- I'm sorry.
- You get how we feel now, right?

401
00:13:44,838 --> 00:13:46,237
Among the members,

402
00:13:46,238 --> 00:13:48,237
Seon Ho and I are the best at jump rope.

403
00:13:48,238 --> 00:13:49,767
- Seon Ho is good.
- At my elementary school,

404
00:13:49,768 --> 00:13:52,077
- We just need one more person.
- I won first place for jump rope.

405
00:13:52,078 --> 00:13:54,547
- Let's hold a tryout for jump rope.
- Let's do it.

406
00:13:54,548 --> 00:13:56,707
- We need at least 5 minutes.
- At least 5 minutes?

407
00:13:56,708 --> 00:13:57,977
- You two should try it.
- Yes.

408
00:13:57,978 --> 00:13:59,247
You two will try out for jump rope.

409
00:13:59,248 --> 00:14:00,587
I'm not sure if he'll be good. He's so tall.

410
00:14:00,588 --> 00:14:02,148
- Right. You're tall.
- That won't be easy.

411
00:14:02,248 --> 00:14:04,158
(The tryout begins.)

412
00:14:04,888 --> 00:14:07,327
- He's good.
- He's jumping too early.

413
00:14:07,328 --> 00:14:09,687
- But his movements are light.
- He's pretty good.

414
00:14:09,688 --> 00:14:12,298
His movements are quite light.

415
00:14:12,398 --> 00:14:14,228
- Jae Won is great.
- He ought to.

416
00:14:14,298 --> 00:14:15,697
I thought Jae Won was good.

417
00:14:15,698 --> 00:14:16,967
- Not bad at all.
- Not bad?

418
00:14:16,968 --> 00:14:18,497
- The three of us should try it.
- Yes.

419
00:14:18,498 --> 00:14:19,637
- You three should try it.
- Go ahead.

420
00:14:19,638 --> 00:14:20,707
Go.

421
00:14:20,708 --> 00:14:21,708
(The three of them try it together.)

422
00:14:21,709 --> 00:14:22,967
- One. Okay. Slow down.
- Okay.

423
00:14:22,968 --> 00:14:24,207
- In the end, - Don't be nervous.

424
00:14:24,208 --> 00:14:25,337
- the rope will get stuck.
- Don't jump too high.

425
00:14:25,338 --> 00:14:26,477
- There you go.
- That's good.

426
00:14:26,478 --> 00:14:27,478
- Get into the rhythm.
- Great.

427
00:14:27,479 --> 00:14:28,877
- They got it.
- We got it.

428
00:14:28,878 --> 00:14:29,947
- Stop.
- Okay.

429
00:14:29,948 --> 00:14:31,217
- We got it, right?
- Jae Won's movements are light.

430
00:14:31,218 --> 00:14:32,517
The three of them make a good team.

431
00:14:32,518 --> 00:14:34,147
- The three of you should do it.
- That was perfect.

432
00:14:34,148 --> 00:14:35,417
We're done looking. The three of them will do it.

433
00:14:35,418 --> 00:14:37,887
- Can the four of you stand here?
- Sure.

434
00:14:37,888 --> 00:14:39,717
The three of you can stand next to the rope.

435
00:14:39,718 --> 00:14:41,487
- Jong Min. You and I should...
- I'll move quickly.

436
00:14:41,488 --> 00:14:42,488
- toss them the items.
- Yes.

437
00:14:42,489 --> 00:14:44,457
- We know what we're going to need.
- Yes.

438
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:45,557
- We'll toss them to you.
- We'll work on the ground.

439
00:14:45,558 --> 00:14:47,728
- The two of you can carry things.
- Okay.

440
00:14:47,898 --> 00:14:49,367
- You have to be really quick.
- We can do it.

441
00:14:49,368 --> 00:14:50,867
- I'll tell you what.
- You can just...

442
00:14:50,868 --> 00:14:53,197
We can't last longer than 2 or 3 minutes.

443
00:14:53,198 --> 00:14:55,168
- The ground here is really uneven.
- It's really uneven.

444
00:14:55,368 --> 00:14:56,608
Take a lot of them out.

445
00:14:56,978 --> 00:14:58,137
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

446
00:14:58,138 --> 00:15:01,007
I'll give you ten seconds to scan inside the truck.

447
00:15:01,008 --> 00:15:02,377
- That sounds great.
- And...

448
00:15:02,378 --> 00:15:04,617
after the ten seconds, you'll begin. The moment you begin,

449
00:15:04,618 --> 00:15:07,217
they will swing the rope. That's when everything will count.

450
00:15:07,218 --> 00:15:08,718
All right. Here it goes.

451
00:15:09,188 --> 00:15:10,887
Open the truck!

452
00:15:10,888 --> 00:15:12,857
- Let's look closely.
- Focus!

453
00:15:12,858 --> 00:15:14,557
- We must do a good job.
- Keep your eyes open!

454
00:15:14,558 --> 00:15:16,427
- You only focus on the rope.
- Okay.

455
00:15:16,428 --> 00:15:18,758
- Get everything on the left.
- Where are the sleeping bags?

456
00:15:19,158 --> 00:15:21,267
(Checking the location of the sleeping bags)

457
00:15:21,268 --> 00:15:23,267
- Get everything on the left.
- Get the mats.

458
00:15:23,268 --> 00:15:24,667
Get the mats and boxes no matter what.

459
00:15:24,668 --> 00:15:27,067
Can't I go to sleep while hugging the doll?

460
00:15:27,068 --> 00:15:28,108
There it is.

461
00:15:28,638 --> 00:15:30,067
Do you see the Styrofoam?

462
00:15:30,068 --> 00:15:31,108
- We can put it on the ground.
- Styrofoam?

463
00:15:31,378 --> 00:15:33,007
- Five, four, - Is that the sleeping bag?

464
00:15:33,008 --> 00:15:35,148
- We need those things.
- three, two...

465
00:15:35,378 --> 00:15:36,478
Get ready.

466
00:15:37,248 --> 00:15:39,548
The temperature keeps dropping. Right?

467
00:15:40,188 --> 00:15:44,118
(To survive in this brutal cold,)

468
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:48,688
(they must grab as many items as they can.)

469
00:15:48,928 --> 00:15:50,627
You only get one chance.

470
00:15:50,628 --> 00:15:52,428
(They only get one chance.)

471
00:15:52,658 --> 00:15:53,998
Se Yoon, we believe in you.

472
00:15:54,798 --> 00:15:56,668
- Let's line up.
- Okay.

473
00:15:56,798 --> 00:15:58,798
(Nervous)

474
00:15:58,998 --> 00:16:01,068
(Will they be able to bring the items they want?)

475
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:03,337
(They start raiding the props on the truck.)

476
00:16:03,338 --> 00:16:04,407
Run.

477
00:16:04,408 --> 00:16:06,277
(Charging toward the truck with the props)

478
00:16:06,278 --> 00:16:08,108
- Hurry up.
- We must bring them down.

479
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:09,977
(Quickly arriving at the truck)

480
00:16:09,978 --> 00:16:11,248
We need to bring down the tools.

481
00:16:11,718 --> 00:16:13,317
Hey, help me up.

482
00:16:13,318 --> 00:16:14,388
What's this?

483
00:16:14,748 --> 00:16:15,947
(They start jumping rope.)

484
00:16:15,948 --> 00:16:17,358
Things are going well for us.

485
00:16:17,558 --> 00:16:20,428
(The moment they mess up, the mission is over.)

486
00:16:20,928 --> 00:16:23,558
(Maximum focus)

487
00:16:24,058 --> 00:16:25,097
Sleeping bags!

488
00:16:25,098 --> 00:16:26,698
(They grab the sleeping bags first.)

489
00:16:27,468 --> 00:16:28,927
(They quickly bring down the items.)

490
00:16:28,928 --> 00:16:29,928
(Materials for insulation)

491
00:16:30,398 --> 00:16:31,468
Blankets.

492
00:16:31,898 --> 00:16:33,607
(Materials for insulation)

493
00:16:33,608 --> 00:16:34,738
(They start moving the items.)

494
00:16:35,168 --> 00:16:37,538
(Delivering the doll Jong Min wanted despite being busy)

495
00:16:37,878 --> 00:16:39,408
Grab the sleeping bags!

496
00:16:39,608 --> 00:16:42,607
(Swiftly delivering the essentials, sleeping bags)

497
00:16:42,608 --> 00:16:44,818
(Busily moving his hands and feet)

498
00:16:45,548 --> 00:16:47,518
(Mattress toppers)

499
00:16:47,718 --> 00:16:50,418
(They have been jumping rope for 30 seconds now.)

500
00:16:51,318 --> 00:16:53,957
(They're hanging in there without messing up so far.)

501
00:16:53,958 --> 00:16:55,928
(Jae Won jumps lightly with full of energy.)

502
00:16:56,328 --> 00:16:59,757
(Incredible jumping skills)

503
00:16:59,758 --> 00:17:02,027
(He's finally showing off his athletic side.)

504
00:17:02,028 --> 00:17:03,398
We're getting tired!

505
00:17:04,298 --> 00:17:06,337
(His skinny legs are getting fatigued.)

506
00:17:06,338 --> 00:17:07,967
No! You can't be tired yet.

507
00:17:07,968 --> 00:17:09,768
Hang in there a little longer.

508
00:17:10,068 --> 00:17:11,537
(Speeding up at the news of fatigue)

509
00:17:11,538 --> 00:17:12,808
You can't get tired yet!

510
00:17:13,378 --> 00:17:14,708
Here's a pickax!

511
00:17:15,138 --> 00:17:16,208
Great!

512
00:17:16,248 --> 00:17:17,578
(They speed up the deliveries too.)

513
00:17:17,748 --> 00:17:19,247
(Boxes for the house)

514
00:17:19,248 --> 00:17:20,517
- Toss them.
- Let's go.

515
00:17:20,518 --> 00:17:21,717
(They've brought a lot of items already.)

516
00:17:21,718 --> 00:17:23,117
Come down now.

517
00:17:23,118 --> 00:17:25,218
(It's already been 1 minute.)

518
00:17:25,718 --> 00:17:27,157
(They can't jump as high as before.)

519
00:17:27,158 --> 00:17:28,558
(Panting)

520
00:17:29,658 --> 00:17:31,828
(Their legs are going numb too.)

521
00:17:32,158 --> 00:17:33,297
We're tired!

522
00:17:33,298 --> 00:17:36,098
(They keep jumping even though they're tired.)

523
00:17:36,298 --> 00:17:38,268
Not yet! No!

524
00:17:38,838 --> 00:17:40,608
We need this.

525
00:17:41,008 --> 00:17:43,467
(Quickly delivering as many items as possible)

526
00:17:43,468 --> 00:17:45,008
- We must move them.
- Let's go.

527
00:17:45,338 --> 00:17:46,677
Bring down the tableware.

528
00:17:46,678 --> 00:17:47,877
(Jong Min joins Team Delivery too.)

529
00:17:47,878 --> 00:17:49,708
(They've been jumping for 1 minute and 25 seconds.)

530
00:17:50,078 --> 00:17:51,747
(They're gradually reaching their limit now.)

531
00:17:51,748 --> 00:17:53,378
- I'm tired!
- No.

532
00:17:53,578 --> 00:17:54,788
No!

533
00:17:54,991 --> 00:17:56,021
My gosh.

534
00:17:57,018 --> 00:17:59,888
(He can't last any longer. His foot gets caught in the rope.)

535
00:18:00,928 --> 00:18:02,828
What?

536
00:18:03,488 --> 00:18:05,228
(Sneakily adding the pots to the pile)

537
00:18:05,298 --> 00:18:07,197
(Exhausted)

538
00:18:07,198 --> 00:18:09,498
- They count too.
- I might pass out. I'm tired.

539
00:18:09,683 --> 00:18:11,367
- Well done.
- We did a great job.

540
00:18:11,368 --> 00:18:12,397
We were amazing.

541
00:18:12,398 --> 00:18:14,868
- We lasted a long time.
- Jae Won was good too.

542
00:18:15,368 --> 00:18:17,277
(They're done grabbing the items.)

543
00:18:17,278 --> 00:18:18,377
I'm tired.

544
00:18:18,378 --> 00:18:20,408
(Current temperature: Minus 15°C)

545
00:18:21,278 --> 00:18:23,978
(They must build a base camp to shelter from the cold.)

546
00:18:24,518 --> 00:18:25,748
What did we grab?

547
00:18:26,248 --> 00:18:27,648
We grabbed a lot of things.

548
00:18:28,088 --> 00:18:30,687
Some of the materials will keep us warm throughout the night.

549
00:18:30,688 --> 00:18:31,414
Blankets.

550
00:18:32,558 --> 00:18:34,912
We also got the plastic sheets. For the cover.

551
00:18:35,118 --> 00:18:36,187
We need to set it up.

552
00:18:36,212 --> 00:18:38,012
- We can't.
- We can use the boxes.

553
00:18:38,458 --> 00:18:39,727
- Let's make a house with boxes.
- But the thing is,

554
00:18:39,728 --> 00:18:42,227
boxes fall more easily than you think.

555
00:18:42,228 --> 00:18:43,838
I see. What do we do then?

556
00:18:44,368 --> 00:18:47,537
Everyone, you're done obtaining materials for the night.

557
00:18:47,538 --> 00:18:48,235
Okay.

558
00:18:48,529 --> 00:18:50,168
You can build a base camp...

559
00:18:50,169 --> 00:18:52,024
with the items you obtained.

560
00:18:52,145 --> 00:18:54,414
- Let's start making the fire.
- Okay.

561
00:18:54,415 --> 00:18:55,914
- So we can rest while working.
- Okay.

562
00:18:55,915 --> 00:18:57,384
We need to get the fire going first.

563
00:18:57,385 --> 00:18:58,685
It's cold, so let's put it in the front.

564
00:18:59,785 --> 00:19:00,814
- Right here?
- Yes.

565
00:19:00,815 --> 00:19:02,385
(It seems the guests have accepted their fate.)

566
00:19:02,555 --> 00:19:04,585
- I'll go and grab the firewood.
- Yes. Let's grab it.

567
00:19:04,725 --> 00:19:05,955
(This is the bonfire zone.)

568
00:19:06,325 --> 00:19:08,254
(Working hard)

569
00:19:08,255 --> 00:19:10,064
- Are they small enough to fit?
- Like this...

570
00:19:10,065 --> 00:19:11,794
- Give them to me.
- Shouldn't they be narrow?

571
00:19:11,795 --> 00:19:13,424
- You've never started a fire?
- No.

572
00:19:13,449 --> 00:19:15,809
- We can start a fire here.
- Yes.

573
00:19:16,139 --> 00:19:18,064
We don't know where we'll build the house.

574
00:19:18,065 --> 00:19:19,574
- What will you do with that?
- What?

575
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:20,145
What?

576
00:19:20,975 --> 00:19:22,535
- What?
- What are you doing?

577
00:19:22,945 --> 00:19:24,245
- Do this.
- Okay.

578
00:19:24,918 --> 00:19:26,388
- Cut the wood like this.
- Okay.

579
00:19:26,675 --> 00:19:28,644
- You must start a fire with this.
- He's right.

580
00:19:28,645 --> 00:19:30,485
- It won't work if it's thick.
- Right.

581
00:19:31,645 --> 00:19:34,284
(His 19 years of experience on 2 Days 1 Night)

582
00:19:34,285 --> 00:19:35,384
- Okay.
- I see.

583
00:19:35,385 --> 00:19:37,685
(The winter training beginners are learning.)

584
00:19:38,325 --> 00:19:39,824
- Do you see this piece?
- Yes.

585
00:19:39,825 --> 00:19:41,655
Cut it like this.

586
00:19:41,925 --> 00:19:44,125
It became thin. Unless it's thin...

587
00:19:44,395 --> 00:19:46,695
Do you see the thin pieces? Start a fire with these first.

588
00:19:47,165 --> 00:19:48,194
Be careful with your hands.

589
00:19:48,195 --> 00:19:50,265
- We'll start a fire here.
- Okay.

590
00:19:51,505 --> 00:19:52,905
Where should we build a house?

591
00:19:53,635 --> 00:19:56,174
How shall we build a house?

592
00:19:56,175 --> 00:19:57,474
We need a plan.

593
00:19:57,475 --> 00:19:59,844
Boom, don't you know about buildings?

594
00:19:59,845 --> 00:20:01,274
- Yes, I do.
- What was your major?

595
00:20:01,275 --> 00:20:02,315
What?

596
00:20:02,885 --> 00:20:04,584
- What was your major?
- I really enjoyed...

597
00:20:04,585 --> 00:20:06,085
watching the movie "Architecture 101."

598
00:20:06,285 --> 00:20:07,555
Let me explain.

599
00:20:08,115 --> 00:20:09,255
Okay.

600
00:20:10,485 --> 00:20:12,225
- What should we do?
- First, we must decide the shape.

601
00:20:12,385 --> 00:20:13,794
- The shape?
- Will it be rectangular...

602
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:15,124
or a house with a thatched roof?

603
00:20:15,125 --> 00:20:16,625
- Rectangular...
- We must shape it with wood.

604
00:20:16,925 --> 00:20:20,665
We lost during our winter training last year.

605
00:20:20,965 --> 00:20:22,664
We ended up building a house with paper.

606
00:20:22,665 --> 00:20:23,904
We covered it with tarpaulin.

607
00:20:23,905 --> 00:20:25,805
When the paper house collapsed,

608
00:20:26,105 --> 00:20:28,904
the ceiling came down. It felt so claustrophobic...

609
00:20:28,905 --> 00:20:30,974
that two people claimed to have seen a ghost at night.

610
00:20:30,975 --> 00:20:33,074
I'd like the ceiling to be high this time.

611
00:20:33,075 --> 00:20:34,874
And so...

612
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:36,985
- Like the Mongolians in the past...
- A Mongolian yurt.

613
00:20:37,115 --> 00:20:38,315
That would be the best.

614
00:20:38,685 --> 00:20:40,214
- The Mongolian style? Okay.
- The Mongolian style.

615
00:20:40,215 --> 00:20:41,415
- Would it be possible?
- Yes.

616
00:20:41,585 --> 00:20:43,354
- To build a yurt...
- There are seven of us.

617
00:20:43,355 --> 00:20:44,524
Seven people have to sleep together.

618
00:20:44,525 --> 00:20:46,524
We have to build that in order to make a yurt.

619
00:20:46,525 --> 00:20:47,525
- Look.
- What?

620
00:20:47,526 --> 00:20:49,295
Underneath something long,

621
00:20:49,425 --> 00:20:52,125
we have to attach a tripod just like that.

622
00:20:52,795 --> 00:20:54,664
- We can use that as a roof.
- Exactly.

623
00:20:54,665 --> 00:20:55,934
Let's use that.

624
00:20:55,935 --> 00:20:57,664
- Will it fall down?
- Yes.

625
00:20:57,665 --> 00:20:59,534
We'll make a tent like this.

626
00:20:59,535 --> 00:21:00,535
Let's bring it.

627
00:21:00,536 --> 00:21:01,935
- Let's use this.
- Okay.

628
00:21:02,235 --> 00:21:04,845
- This won't collapse.
- It will never collapse.

629
00:21:05,105 --> 00:21:07,044
Let's take it. One, two, three.

630
00:21:07,045 --> 00:21:08,475
(The base camp construction team is off to a good start.)

631
00:21:09,045 --> 00:21:10,744
(Meanwhile, the fire-starting team...)

632
00:21:10,745 --> 00:21:11,785
Like this.

633
00:21:12,345 --> 00:21:13,415
(Blowing)

634
00:21:14,055 --> 00:21:16,015
(Blowing)

635
00:21:18,225 --> 00:21:19,995
It's harder to start a fire than I thought.

636
00:21:21,025 --> 00:21:22,595
That's it. Tap it slowly.

637
00:21:23,325 --> 00:21:24,325
That's good.

638
00:21:24,765 --> 00:21:25,994
(Piling up)

639
00:21:25,995 --> 00:21:26,995
Good job.

640
00:21:27,235 --> 00:21:28,335
Did it start?

641
00:21:28,635 --> 00:21:30,065
I guess there wasn't any air inside.

642
00:21:30,765 --> 00:21:32,304
- The firewood is...
- This is done.

643
00:21:32,305 --> 00:21:33,435
frozen.

644
00:21:34,235 --> 00:21:36,405
(The firewood is frozen, and the setup looks like a mess.)

645
00:21:36,805 --> 00:21:38,005
It stings my eyes.

646
00:21:41,775 --> 00:21:43,815
Give that to me. Let me show you.

647
00:21:44,315 --> 00:21:45,415
Can you hold these?

648
00:21:46,185 --> 00:21:48,115
(Is Jong Min stepping in once again?)

649
00:21:48,215 --> 00:21:49,724
- The flame died out.
- Wait a minute.

650
00:21:49,725 --> 00:21:51,055
No, it didn't die out.

651
00:21:51,325 --> 00:21:54,055
(Fanning)

652
00:21:54,255 --> 00:21:55,894
- You have to do this.
- The fire is starting.

653
00:21:55,895 --> 00:21:58,064
- He started a fire.
- You guys...

654
00:21:58,065 --> 00:22:00,035
If you knew how to do it, why didn't you help us earlier?

655
00:22:00,895 --> 00:22:01,964
Why...

656
00:22:01,965 --> 00:22:03,764
I wanted to see what you'd do.

657
00:22:03,765 --> 00:22:04,864
(In the extreme land at minus 15°C,)

658
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:05,865
(a master of fire appeared.)

659
00:22:06,435 --> 00:22:08,375
- Should we add more firewood?
- Wait.

660
00:22:09,575 --> 00:22:11,144
- We have to sleep outside.
- Yes.

661
00:22:11,145 --> 00:22:12,774
If we don't make it well, we'll regret it.

662
00:22:12,775 --> 00:22:13,874
What do we have here?

663
00:22:13,875 --> 00:22:15,745
(Meanwhile, the house building team is exploring the articles.)

664
00:22:15,945 --> 00:22:17,215
We have wooden beams.

665
00:22:17,485 --> 00:22:19,084
- We have wooden beams.
- What should we do with them?

666
00:22:19,085 --> 00:22:20,085
What?

667
00:22:20,185 --> 00:22:22,155
We should use wooden beams to build support.

668
00:22:22,415 --> 00:22:23,855
- Support?
- Do we also have wooden beams?

669
00:22:24,585 --> 00:22:25,855
Over here like this?

670
00:22:27,125 --> 00:22:29,324
- I see.
- We should put it like this.

671
00:22:29,325 --> 00:22:31,264
We can create a structure.

672
00:22:31,265 --> 00:22:33,065
Do we have enough wooden beams to build that?

673
00:22:33,395 --> 00:22:34,465
Like that?

674
00:22:34,535 --> 00:22:37,365
(DinDin and Jae Won join the house building team.)

675
00:22:37,665 --> 00:22:39,575
Will this be the ceiling?

676
00:22:40,035 --> 00:22:41,834
That's the plan. There's nothing else we can use.

677
00:22:41,835 --> 00:22:43,305
(Making the ceiling with the banner)

678
00:22:43,705 --> 00:22:45,374
- Put on some tape. Give it to them.
- Put it on.

679
00:22:45,375 --> 00:22:46,545
It's inside the blue box.

680
00:22:46,675 --> 00:22:48,475
Should I use tape or string?

681
00:22:48,745 --> 00:22:50,685
Do we have any strings?

682
00:22:50,985 --> 00:22:52,314
Use what we're undoing.

683
00:22:52,315 --> 00:22:53,414
- Shall we keep it?
- Keep it.

684
00:22:53,415 --> 00:22:54,584
- Would it be strong enough?
- Yes.

685
00:22:54,585 --> 00:22:56,384
If it's strong enough to hold this, it'll be fine.

686
00:22:56,385 --> 00:22:57,625
It's much better than the string.

687
00:22:58,225 --> 00:22:59,955
Should I wrap it around?

688
00:23:00,125 --> 00:23:01,695
Diagonally.

689
00:23:02,225 --> 00:23:03,764
We have to recycle as much as possible.

690
00:23:03,765 --> 00:23:04,895
We can't waste any tape either.

691
00:23:05,265 --> 00:23:07,235
(Securing the beams with wrapping paper)

692
00:23:07,835 --> 00:23:08,894
(Everyone is concentrating on building a house.)

693
00:23:08,895 --> 00:23:10,305
One more time. One, two.

694
00:23:12,435 --> 00:23:14,805
That's it. You improved a lot.

695
00:23:14,975 --> 00:23:16,234
Should we help the others now?

696
00:23:16,235 --> 00:23:17,575
Yes, let's go and help them.

697
00:23:18,605 --> 00:23:19,945
Go and help them. I'll watch the fire.

698
00:23:21,375 --> 00:23:23,444
(The fire)

699
00:23:23,445 --> 00:23:24,445
This is too...

700
00:23:24,446 --> 00:23:26,414
(It's his plan to take a break.)

701
00:23:26,415 --> 00:23:28,084
Jong Min, the fire looks good now. Come here.

702
00:23:28,085 --> 00:23:29,625
Really? Okay.

703
00:23:30,925 --> 00:23:33,035
- Go back and forth.
- Okay, that looks good.

704
00:23:33,525 --> 00:23:36,794
We have to make it like this on the other side.

705
00:23:36,795 --> 00:23:37,895
- Jae Won.
- Yes?

706
00:23:38,065 --> 00:23:39,264
Wrap this with tape.

707
00:23:39,265 --> 00:23:40,764
It should support the weight.

708
00:23:40,765 --> 00:23:41,835
Also on this side.

709
00:23:42,365 --> 00:23:43,705
- So that we can turn it?
- Yes.

710
00:23:44,365 --> 00:23:45,365
Yes.

711
00:23:45,765 --> 00:23:47,034
- Jae Won.
- Yes?

712
00:23:47,035 --> 00:23:48,774
Can you tear some tape for Boom over here?

713
00:23:48,775 --> 00:23:49,805
Okay.

714
00:23:52,045 --> 00:23:53,145
Jae Won.

715
00:23:53,215 --> 00:23:55,915
- Yes?
- Give some tape to DinDin.

716
00:23:56,215 --> 00:23:57,415
- This one.
- Where's the tape?

717
00:23:57,845 --> 00:23:59,085
Jae Won, come this way.

718
00:23:59,215 --> 00:24:01,115
- Jae Won, take a look at this.
- Jae Won.

719
00:24:01,285 --> 00:24:02,914
Jae Won, is there another hammer?

720
00:24:02,915 --> 00:24:04,155
Jae Won, can you take this?

721
00:24:04,285 --> 00:24:05,325
Jae Won!

722
00:24:06,595 --> 00:24:08,054
- Don't you want to act?
- What?

723
00:24:08,055 --> 00:24:10,565
- Don't you want to act instead?
- I miss the set.

724
00:24:11,525 --> 00:24:13,935
Jae Won says he misses being on drama sets.

725
00:24:15,265 --> 00:24:17,035
(Sniffling)

726
00:24:17,365 --> 00:24:19,565
This won't collapse at all.

727
00:24:19,975 --> 00:24:21,575
This is good.

728
00:24:21,875 --> 00:24:23,305
Good job.

729
00:24:23,545 --> 00:24:25,404
Jong Min, can you take care of the cover?

730
00:24:25,405 --> 00:24:26,575
- The cover?
- It's behind you.

731
00:24:26,775 --> 00:24:29,145
- Okay.
- Can you cut the cover?

732
00:24:29,175 --> 00:24:30,314
Please hold it.

733
00:24:30,315 --> 00:24:31,844
Where is the door?

734
00:24:31,845 --> 00:24:33,754
- It's on both sides.
- Both sides?

735
00:24:33,755 --> 00:24:35,384
We'll cover it with mattress toppers.

736
00:24:35,385 --> 00:24:37,584
- Shall I start from the top?
- We only need to cover the top.

737
00:24:37,585 --> 00:24:38,625
Okay.

738
00:24:38,825 --> 00:24:40,024
Will the seven of us fit?

739
00:24:40,025 --> 00:24:41,155
Shouldn't we test it by lying down?

740
00:24:41,755 --> 00:24:43,165
Wait a minute.

741
00:24:45,395 --> 00:24:47,965
(Why are they measuring the space so late?)

742
00:24:49,935 --> 00:24:51,035
Is it okay?

743
00:24:53,075 --> 00:24:54,174
It won't work.

744
00:24:54,175 --> 00:24:56,235
- One of us has to sleep outside.
- One will be outside.

745
00:24:57,405 --> 00:24:58,744
- The maximum is six people.
- One, two.

746
00:24:58,745 --> 00:25:00,444
- Stay close to each other.
- Get closer.

747
00:25:00,445 --> 00:25:01,545
Can you move this way?

748
00:25:01,815 --> 00:25:03,945
It was very cramped last year.

749
00:25:04,185 --> 00:25:05,244
We thought that it was okay at first.

750
00:25:05,245 --> 00:25:06,484
There isn't enough space.

751
00:25:06,485 --> 00:25:07,754
- What do you mean?
- It's just not enough.

752
00:25:07,755 --> 00:25:09,014
Someone will get stuck between the legs.

753
00:25:09,015 --> 00:25:10,584
- You will?
- The stand has legs.

754
00:25:10,585 --> 00:25:11,984
- Where?
- No, I mean here...

755
00:25:11,985 --> 00:25:13,494
- One, two, three, four.
- The legs of the stand.

756
00:25:13,495 --> 00:25:14,995
- Someone would touch the stand.
- Exactly.

757
00:25:15,125 --> 00:25:16,724
Someone can put his legs...

758
00:25:16,725 --> 00:25:18,625
between the legs of the stand.

759
00:25:18,965 --> 00:25:21,695
Someone unlucky will sleep at the end.

760
00:25:22,495 --> 00:25:24,505
- Shall we lie down sideways?
- How?

761
00:25:24,718 --> 00:25:26,048
Why don't we sleep by facing this way?

762
00:25:26,505 --> 00:25:28,175
- That's the only solution.
- Let's lie down sideways.

763
00:25:28,635 --> 00:25:29,944
Let's lie down sideways.

764
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:31,675
(He was being serious.)

765
00:25:32,545 --> 00:25:34,244
(How problems are solved on 2 Days 1 Night)

766
00:25:34,245 --> 00:25:35,275
Let's try it.

767
00:25:37,215 --> 00:25:38,484
- Does it look okay?
- There's enough space.

768
00:25:38,485 --> 00:25:39,884
- Is it enough?
- It's enough.

769
00:25:39,885 --> 00:25:41,784
- Problem solved.
- I usually sleep curled up.

770
00:25:41,785 --> 00:25:42,885
Okay.

771
00:25:44,085 --> 00:25:45,484
- Se Yoon. This...
- Wait.

772
00:25:45,485 --> 00:25:46,824
Before nailing it down to the ground,

773
00:25:46,825 --> 00:25:49,395
I'll roll it inward to block the wind.

774
00:25:49,895 --> 00:25:51,065
Okay, that's good.

775
00:25:51,525 --> 00:25:53,234
- Like this?
- Overlap them slightly.

776
00:25:53,235 --> 00:25:54,235
Okay.

777
00:25:54,236 --> 00:25:55,795
(The base camp gets built smoothly under Director Boom's command.)

778
00:25:56,665 --> 00:25:58,164
We're good at making a house.

779
00:25:58,165 --> 00:25:59,235
(The house is almost complete.)

780
00:25:59,565 --> 00:26:00,874
Be careful with your hands.

781
00:26:00,875 --> 00:26:01,875
(At that moment)

782
00:26:04,205 --> 00:26:05,474
- Okay.
- Did you hear that?

783
00:26:05,475 --> 00:26:06,475
The sound...

784
00:26:06,775 --> 00:26:09,884
(It's an actual sound without exaggeration.)

785
00:26:09,885 --> 00:26:11,684
- I like the sound.
- Goodness.

786
00:26:11,685 --> 00:26:12,844
- It's because the ground is frozen.
- Let me see.

787
00:26:12,845 --> 00:26:14,455
(The ground is completely frozen.)

788
00:26:15,155 --> 00:26:16,655
Was that the actual sound?

789
00:26:18,485 --> 00:26:20,154
(The weather is getting colder.)

790
00:26:20,155 --> 00:26:21,695
(Reaching minus 17°C)

791
00:26:22,225 --> 00:26:24,024
We could die from sleeping here.

792
00:26:24,025 --> 00:26:25,525
- Die from what?
- Will it be okay?

793
00:26:26,025 --> 00:26:28,595
It looks like one of us may not wake up tomorrow.

794
00:26:29,735 --> 00:26:31,104
Guys, let's put out the tarpaulin.

795
00:26:31,105 --> 00:26:32,705
- Go in from the back.
- From where?

796
00:26:32,974 --> 00:26:33,774
Here?

797
00:26:34,575 --> 00:26:36,775
- Come in without touching anything.
- Pull it all the way in.

798
00:26:36,945 --> 00:26:38,305
- Give me a second.
- Okay.

799
00:26:39,675 --> 00:26:41,345
This will need some work.

800
00:26:41,775 --> 00:26:42,845
Wait.

801
00:26:44,345 --> 00:26:45,784
We should've covered the ground first.

802
00:26:45,785 --> 00:26:46,954
We should've done that first.

803
00:26:46,955 --> 00:26:48,955
- What kind of construction is this?
- I know.

804
00:26:50,125 --> 00:26:51,454
(Boom's experience is watching "Architecture 101.")

805
00:26:51,455 --> 00:26:52,685
It's okay. We can do it.

806
00:26:53,525 --> 00:26:55,195
I'll pull it on this side.

807
00:26:55,495 --> 00:26:58,224
I'll pull it. We can do it.

808
00:26:58,225 --> 00:26:59,495
(Director Boom steps in to calm down the angry residents.)

809
00:26:59,625 --> 00:27:02,294
(With Boom's help, they laid down the floor roughly.)

810
00:27:02,295 --> 00:27:05,165
It doesn't look right. We're in trouble.

811
00:27:06,165 --> 00:27:08,604
There's a rock. Gosh, my knee.

812
00:27:08,605 --> 00:27:11,405
(He can feel the rocks on the floor.)

813
00:27:11,845 --> 00:27:13,074
(A side effect of a rushed construction)

814
00:27:13,075 --> 00:27:15,045
(While Se Yoon is unconscious momentarily)

815
00:27:15,415 --> 00:27:17,745
- Okay.
- A break for five minutes.

816
00:27:18,545 --> 00:27:19,715
Take a break for five minutes.

817
00:27:20,415 --> 00:27:22,384
Boom, do you want these back...

818
00:27:22,385 --> 00:27:23,755
so that you can find strength again?

819
00:27:24,625 --> 00:27:25,824
So you can find strength again.

820
00:27:25,825 --> 00:27:26,925
- What?
- Your phone.

821
00:27:27,095 --> 00:27:28,425
And the speaker?

822
00:27:29,395 --> 00:27:30,965
It's true that I'm tired.

823
00:27:31,525 --> 00:27:33,125
- Okay.
- Here you go.

824
00:27:33,665 --> 00:27:35,865
(At that moment)

825
00:27:36,705 --> 00:27:38,065
Excuse me, Mr. Architect.

826
00:27:38,665 --> 00:27:39,665
Yes?

827
00:27:40,205 --> 00:27:41,404
(It's a customer who's about to make a complaint.)

828
00:27:41,405 --> 00:27:43,075
- Something seems off.
- What's wrong?

829
00:27:43,275 --> 00:27:44,375
- What's the problem?
- This...

830
00:27:44,845 --> 00:27:46,205
It may look okay now, but...

831
00:27:46,345 --> 00:27:48,515
Let's not talk about work when we're taking a break.

832
00:27:48,775 --> 00:27:51,285
(He's on vacation at a crucial moment.)

833
00:27:51,415 --> 00:27:52,715
- What's this?
- Let's relax.

834
00:27:53,145 --> 00:27:55,414
- We can be romantic, can't we?
- What's this?

835
00:27:55,415 --> 00:27:57,125
- Are we allowed to take a break?
- Yes.

836
00:27:57,425 --> 00:27:59,454
We can be romantic. Let's take a break with romance.

837
00:27:59,455 --> 00:28:02,595
(The sweet music seems out of place in this desolate area.)

838
00:28:03,055 --> 00:28:04,165
It feels hot.

839
00:28:04,665 --> 00:28:06,025
It's minus 15°C, but it feels hot.

840
00:28:07,965 --> 00:28:09,064
This is lovely.

841
00:28:09,065 --> 00:28:10,364
(Jukebox Boom is playing.)

842
00:28:10,365 --> 00:28:12,265
(He loves it.)

843
00:28:15,275 --> 00:28:16,335
Goodness.

844
00:28:17,875 --> 00:28:19,704
(A saxophone that he had been hiding)

845
00:28:19,705 --> 00:28:21,015
You told us to take a break.

846
00:28:21,445 --> 00:28:22,445
(Grunting)

847
00:28:23,715 --> 00:28:25,684
(While the older guys enjoy a short break)

848
00:28:25,685 --> 00:28:26,715
You're good at playing.

849
00:28:27,685 --> 00:28:29,214
Can you lift the rock?

850
00:28:29,215 --> 00:28:30,884
- I'll nail it here.
- Okay.

851
00:28:30,885 --> 00:28:32,854
(The younger members are focused on building the house.)

852
00:28:32,855 --> 00:28:34,295
Hello.

853
00:28:34,695 --> 00:28:35,855
What's this?

854
00:28:36,455 --> 00:28:39,465
(He brought out a double bass from the truck with props.)

855
00:28:54,045 --> 00:28:57,244
(Blooming in the wilderness at minus 17°C)

856
00:28:57,245 --> 00:29:02,415
(A performance by an insane trio)

857
00:29:04,485 --> 00:29:06,824
(Jukebox Boom is playing.)

858
00:29:06,825 --> 00:29:08,925
- This is romance.
- I like romance.

859
00:29:09,725 --> 00:29:11,695
- Let's play again next time.
- Okay.

860
00:29:11,925 --> 00:29:13,635
The younger ones don't know how to be romantic.

861
00:29:13,695 --> 00:29:16,535
- Put down your instrument.
- Gosh.

862
00:29:16,935 --> 00:29:18,404
- Boom.
- Yes?

863
00:29:18,405 --> 00:29:20,235
- What do you think?
- It will definitely collapse.

864
00:29:20,735 --> 00:29:22,374
It's impossible not to talk about work.

865
00:29:22,375 --> 00:29:23,404
Is this going to work?

866
00:29:23,405 --> 00:29:25,275
- I mean...
- Director Boom.

867
00:29:25,375 --> 00:29:26,574
What are you planning to do next?

868
00:29:26,575 --> 00:29:28,044
It'll definitely collapse.

869
00:29:28,045 --> 00:29:30,745
We barely put the tarpaulin inside, and it's a huge mess.

870
00:29:31,445 --> 00:29:33,121
What do we do now?

871
00:29:33,224 --> 00:29:35,593
We will cover the top with plastic...

872
00:29:35,618 --> 00:29:36,817
and make a door.

873
00:29:36,955 --> 00:29:40,654
Next, we'll lay down the Styrofoam and sleeping bags.

874
00:29:40,655 --> 00:29:41,924
- Let's get started.
- Okay.

875
00:29:41,925 --> 00:29:43,224
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

876
00:29:43,225 --> 00:29:44,465
- Let's go.
- Okay.

877
00:29:45,195 --> 00:29:46,594
All right. You can do it.

878
00:29:46,595 --> 00:29:47,935
- There's always music.
- We can do it.

879
00:29:48,035 --> 00:29:49,064
Let's do a cheer.

880
00:29:49,065 --> 00:29:51,404
- This feels like a musical.
- Let's go.

881
00:29:51,405 --> 00:29:52,464
(Jukebox Boom is playing.)

882
00:29:52,465 --> 00:29:55,705
("For Victory" by Trans Fixion)

883
00:29:59,405 --> 00:30:02,415
(Anyway, let's go for victory.)

884
00:30:02,645 --> 00:30:03,985
Look straight ahead.

885
00:30:04,285 --> 00:30:05,945
Can you look at the camera for a minute?

886
00:30:08,555 --> 00:30:10,224
(Turning off Jukebox Boom by force for the greater good)

887
00:30:10,225 --> 00:30:11,425
Turn off the music.

888
00:30:12,985 --> 00:30:15,594
- Like this?
- Raise it. Wait.

889
00:30:15,595 --> 00:30:17,125
- Let's wrap it in this direction.
- How?

890
00:30:17,365 --> 00:30:19,364
Go around.

891
00:30:19,365 --> 00:30:20,453
(Director Boom's Revision Plan: Making a door)

892
00:30:20,995 --> 00:30:22,464
(Fixing so that it doesn't get blown away by the wind)

893
00:30:22,465 --> 00:30:23,905
- Okay.
- Great.

894
00:30:24,205 --> 00:30:26,065
- This...
- Seon Ho.

895
00:30:26,665 --> 00:30:28,434
- What is it?
- Cover the ground.

896
00:30:28,435 --> 00:30:29,805
Let's cover the ground with this.

897
00:30:29,975 --> 00:30:32,075
This will stop the draft on the floor.

898
00:30:32,345 --> 00:30:33,844
Wrap it around once.

899
00:30:33,845 --> 00:30:34,874
(Is he planning to get rid of the draft with straw?)

900
00:30:34,875 --> 00:30:37,044
- How will this work?
- What about this?

901
00:30:37,045 --> 00:30:38,944
- Why are we doing this?
- What is this for?

902
00:30:38,945 --> 00:30:41,415
We're not trees on the road.

903
00:30:42,555 --> 00:30:44,124
Let's go. Can you pull it?

904
00:30:44,125 --> 00:30:45,355
- Pull it harder, Jong Min.
- Okay.

905
00:30:46,455 --> 00:30:47,855
Let's wrap it around one more time.

906
00:30:47,955 --> 00:30:49,155
- Okay.
- Make it heavy.

907
00:30:49,295 --> 00:30:50,565
This looks okay.

908
00:30:51,065 --> 00:30:52,795
- Jong Min, you're a genius.
- These...

909
00:30:53,095 --> 00:30:54,934
We made a proper house today.

910
00:30:54,935 --> 00:30:57,164
- Where's the tape?
- It's right here.

911
00:30:57,165 --> 00:30:58,165
The tape.

912
00:30:58,165 --> 00:30:59,165
(Blocking the draft one more time with tape)

913
00:30:59,565 --> 00:31:00,575
The tape.

914
00:31:01,235 --> 00:31:02,875
The tape doesn't stick because it's too cold.

915
00:31:03,875 --> 00:31:04,945
Blow on it.

916
00:31:05,475 --> 00:31:07,575
The tape doesn't stick at all. Touch it.

917
00:31:07,645 --> 00:31:08,875
- It doesn't stick.
- No, it doesn't.

918
00:31:09,775 --> 00:31:11,644
- The tape doesn't stick.
- It really doesn't stick at all.

919
00:31:11,645 --> 00:31:13,215
(Using it by melting it with the fire)

920
00:31:13,785 --> 00:31:15,784
- You can tape it there.
- Here?

921
00:31:15,785 --> 00:31:16,825
Just right here.

922
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:19,384
(They built an exterior wall that will endure minus 17°C.)

923
00:31:19,385 --> 00:31:20,555
It's warm.

924
00:31:20,895 --> 00:31:22,325
Jong Min, it will be warm inside.

925
00:31:22,525 --> 00:31:23,995
We can make it warm.

926
00:31:24,325 --> 00:31:25,895
- This is...
- It will be warm enough.

927
00:31:26,025 --> 00:31:27,064
We got it.

928
00:31:27,065 --> 00:31:28,634
Lie down inside to test it.

929
00:31:28,635 --> 00:31:30,105
Come this way. This is the entrance.

930
00:31:31,365 --> 00:31:33,034
Also, it's like a double window.

931
00:31:33,035 --> 00:31:34,235
There are two layers of door.

932
00:31:35,075 --> 00:31:36,974
(Jae Won comes inside through the double window.)

933
00:31:36,975 --> 00:31:38,475
See if it's cold inside.

934
00:31:39,875 --> 00:31:41,444
(He lies down on the floor.)

935
00:31:41,445 --> 00:31:42,545
Jae Won.

936
00:31:43,045 --> 00:31:45,044
- Lie down. How is it?
- It's really nice.

937
00:31:45,045 --> 00:31:46,114
- Is it really nice?
- Is it nice?

938
00:31:46,115 --> 00:31:47,285
Is it really okay?

939
00:31:47,315 --> 00:31:49,354
He says that it's really nice.

940
00:31:49,355 --> 00:31:50,355
(They won't be scared of the real winter night.)

941
00:31:50,356 --> 00:31:51,725
My gosh.

942
00:31:52,725 --> 00:31:54,225
- Look at that.
- We're done.

943
00:31:54,725 --> 00:31:56,425
We did a good job. It looks nice.

944
00:31:56,895 --> 00:31:58,025
Finally...

945
00:31:58,225 --> 00:31:59,465
How many hours did we take?

946
00:31:59,925 --> 00:32:01,635
- We built it together.
- Good job, everyone.

947
00:32:01,895 --> 00:32:02,964
Say "complete..."

948
00:32:02,965 --> 00:32:04,005
- in the count of three.
- Hey, let's...

949
00:32:04,035 --> 00:32:05,464
- One, two, three.
- Two, three.

950
00:32:05,465 --> 00:32:08,135
(They feel more proud than ever because they worked on it together.)

951
00:32:09,735 --> 00:32:11,975
Let me introduce you today's base camp.

952
00:32:13,245 --> 00:32:16,115
A double layer of straw to block the wind completely.

953
00:32:17,415 --> 00:32:20,255
A plastic front door for security and warmth.

954
00:32:20,715 --> 00:32:24,155
A cozy interior where you can fall asleep instantly.

955
00:32:25,425 --> 00:32:27,895
This is our special base camp.

956
00:32:29,195 --> 00:32:30,664
(Snooping)

957
00:32:30,665 --> 00:32:32,624
- Hey, Jong Min.
- Yes?

958
00:32:32,625 --> 00:32:35,464
It's warm inside like a greenhouse.

959
00:32:35,465 --> 00:32:37,534
At night, our breath will make it...

960
00:32:37,535 --> 00:32:38,765
very toasty inside.

961
00:32:39,005 --> 00:32:40,005
- Jong Min.
- It won't be bad.

962
00:32:40,006 --> 00:32:41,434
It's sealed so tightly...

963
00:32:41,435 --> 00:32:43,774
that we could suffocate from too much carbon dioxide.

964
00:32:43,775 --> 00:32:45,644
- Hey.
- There's no oxygen going in.

965
00:32:45,645 --> 00:32:46,804
- It's not bad.
- It's good.

966
00:32:46,805 --> 00:32:48,274
- No oxygen goes in.
- It's not bad.

967
00:32:48,275 --> 00:32:50,545
- Isn't it warm?
- We can take turns to breathe.

968
00:32:51,385 --> 00:32:52,385
Okay.

969
00:32:52,386 --> 00:32:54,405
- Take turns to breathe?
- Se Yoon, don't breathe a lot.

970
00:32:54,430 --> 00:32:55,076
I won't.

971
00:32:56,115 --> 00:32:57,555
One, two, three.

972
00:32:58,185 --> 00:33:00,825
(2026 Real Winter Special, in front of the house we made)

973
00:33:01,625 --> 00:33:04,095
There was nothing here, but we still built a house.

974
00:33:04,395 --> 00:33:06,164
We created something from nothing.

975
00:33:06,165 --> 00:33:08,834
Everyone, take a break for a minute.

976
00:33:08,835 --> 00:33:10,465
We'll start Dinner Game very soon.

977
00:33:10,635 --> 00:33:13,235
- I'm hungry.
- I'd love some hot ramyeon now.

978
00:33:13,535 --> 00:33:15,174
- It'd be amazing.
- Doesn't ramyeon sound delicious?

979
00:33:15,175 --> 00:33:16,905
Don't they give us food for free?

980
00:33:17,105 --> 00:33:18,505
- I think so.
- No way.

981
00:33:18,705 --> 00:33:20,645
They will never give us food for free.

982
00:33:21,215 --> 00:33:24,215
Here's what I saw while passing by.

983
00:33:24,845 --> 00:33:26,744
I saw 70 to 80 cup noodles.

984
00:33:26,745 --> 00:33:28,654
- Some of them must be for us.
- We'll show how we eat them all.

985
00:33:28,655 --> 00:33:30,454
They can give us a few, can't they?

986
00:33:30,455 --> 00:33:31,984
- I'm craving some hot broth.
- Me too.

987
00:33:31,985 --> 00:33:33,654
We just need ten of them.

988
00:33:33,655 --> 00:33:34,694
(Their mouths are watering.)

989
00:33:34,695 --> 00:33:36,424
Starting now,

990
00:33:36,425 --> 00:33:38,524
with dinner ingredients at stake,

991
00:33:38,525 --> 00:33:40,734
- What is it again?
- Dinner Game will start.

992
00:33:40,735 --> 00:33:43,534
Are you saying that we'll be cooking?

993
00:33:43,535 --> 00:33:44,904
- That's right.
- Really?

994
00:33:44,905 --> 00:33:46,465
- Seriously?
- Boom is good at cooking.

995
00:33:46,865 --> 00:33:48,034
On "Stars' Top Recipe at Fun-Staurant,"

996
00:33:48,035 --> 00:33:49,174
- He's good at cooking.
- he does a lot of cooking.

997
00:33:49,175 --> 00:33:50,675
I also like to cook.

998
00:33:50,945 --> 00:33:52,274
- Are you a good cook?
- I like cooking.

999
00:33:52,275 --> 00:33:54,274
- Do you cook at home?
- Yes.

1000
00:33:54,275 --> 00:33:55,844
It will be a team game...

1001
00:33:55,845 --> 00:33:57,984
- with a total of five rounds.
- A team game?

1002
00:33:57,985 --> 00:33:59,514
- One ingredient is rice.
- Rice?

1003
00:33:59,515 --> 00:34:01,485
- Rice.
- There must be pork belly.

1004
00:34:02,355 --> 00:34:06,325
- One of them is rice.
- You're so cute.

1005
00:34:06,385 --> 00:34:07,894
- Kimchi.
- Kimchi.

1006
00:34:07,895 --> 00:34:08,994
- Kimchi.
- Japanese sandfish.

1007
00:34:08,995 --> 00:34:10,824
- Japanese sandfish?
- That's a must in Gangwon Province.

1008
00:34:10,825 --> 00:34:12,365
There's Japanese sandfish in Gangwon Province.

1009
00:34:13,095 --> 00:34:14,934
- Ramyeon.
- Ramyeon is necessary.

1010
00:34:14,935 --> 00:34:16,695
- And...
- Pork belly?

1011
00:34:17,135 --> 00:34:19,004
- The last is pork belly.
- That's complete.

1012
00:34:19,005 --> 00:34:20,005
- It's complete.
- A lot of pork belly, please.

1013
00:34:20,006 --> 00:34:21,235
All we need is pork belly.

1014
00:34:21,275 --> 00:34:22,734
Let's win ramyeon and pork belly.

1015
00:34:22,735 --> 00:34:25,074
Why don't we get kimchi, pork belly,

1016
00:34:25,075 --> 00:34:26,145
- And ramyeon.
- and ramyeon?

1017
00:34:26,375 --> 00:34:27,815
I want some Japanese sandfish.

1018
00:34:27,975 --> 00:34:29,475
- We must get that too.
- Japanese sandfish.

1019
00:34:29,675 --> 00:34:31,614
Like at a Japanese izakaya,

1020
00:34:31,615 --> 00:34:33,014
with sprinkled salt...

1021
00:34:33,015 --> 00:34:34,884
It's amazing with salt.

1022
00:34:34,885 --> 00:34:37,184
- I'd be happy just with ramyeon.
- Of course.

1023
00:34:37,185 --> 00:34:38,284
