- We did it.

1249
00:41:46,930 --> 00:41:48,959
- Let's do it.
- So I should keep it in the air.

1250
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:50,469
- Let's do it right away.
- Okay.

1251
00:41:50,470 --> 00:41:52,199
- Let's do it as we just did.
- Okay.

1252
00:41:52,200 --> 00:41:53,700
- This is our first attempt.
- Let's begin.

1253
00:41:53,940 --> 00:41:55,740
- Call the ball when you're up.
- Keep it in the air no matter what.

1254
00:41:56,070 --> 00:41:57,209
Let's go. We've got this!

1255
00:41:57,210 --> 00:41:58,439
- We've got this!
- Yes!

1256
00:41:58,440 --> 00:42:00,364
- Wild!
- Wild!

1257
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:02,479
- Okay.
- Okay.

1258
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:03,680
- It's okay.
- Receive the ball.

1259
00:42:03,750 --> 00:42:05,480
(The ball flew in another direction unlike how they planned.)

1260
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:07,549
- Okay. He kicked it. Receive it.
- Mine.

1261
00:42:07,550 --> 00:42:09,990
- Okay. He kicked it.
- Yes! That's good!

1262
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:11,650
(Se Yoon received the ball by heading it.)

1263
00:42:11,890 --> 00:42:13,189
Save the ball. Slowly.

1264
00:42:13,190 --> 00:42:14,190
He kicked it. Receive it.

1265
00:42:14,191 --> 00:42:15,959
We failed because of the light.

1266
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:18,430
We could've succeeded if the staff members weren't here.

1267
00:42:19,460 --> 00:42:20,499
That's right.

1268
00:42:20,500 --> 00:42:21,830
(Jae Won became brazen in a day.)

1269
00:42:22,060 --> 00:42:24,099
You failed in your first attempt.

1270
00:42:24,100 --> 00:42:25,270
That was a practice round.

1271
00:42:25,770 --> 00:42:26,840
- I'm worried.
- Why did you do that?

1272
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:30,769
(He's excited as he's doing what he's good at.)

1273
00:42:30,770 --> 00:42:32,469
But I don't have faith in you even when you call the ball.

1274
00:42:32,470 --> 00:42:33,840
Hold on a second. Seon Ho, come over here.

1275
00:42:33,940 --> 00:42:35,839
I have an idea. Gather around.

1276
00:42:35,840 --> 00:42:37,779
- Gather more closely together.
- Okay.

1277
00:42:37,780 --> 00:42:39,049
- And then we pass the ball.
- I think it'll be difficult.

1278
00:42:39,050 --> 00:42:40,849
- It'll be difficult.
- Let's try it just once.

1279
00:42:40,850 --> 00:42:42,150
- Let's practice.
- Okay.

1280
00:42:43,550 --> 00:42:44,789
(They pass the ball more lightly and quickly now.)

1281
00:42:44,790 --> 00:42:46,089
- Oh, my. It's working.
- I told you.

1282
00:42:46,090 --> 00:42:48,789
- It's easier this way.
- It's working. Let's try this way.

1283
00:42:48,790 --> 00:42:49,989
- It's easier this way.
- Come on.

1284
00:42:49,990 --> 00:42:51,360
(But that's hard to film.)

1285
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:53,529
- Use the camera crane.
- Right.

1286
00:42:53,530 --> 00:42:54,799
Can you film us from up there using the camera crane?

1287
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:56,730
- Yes, they can film us.
- We'll make it.

1288
00:42:56,870 --> 00:42:59,569
- Or one of you can come to film us.
- Let's go.

1289
00:42:59,570 --> 00:43:00,739
- Here we go.
- Is this a real game?

1290
00:43:00,740 --> 00:43:01,969
- We'll start.
- Let's do it.

1291
00:43:01,970 --> 00:43:03,040
We'll start.

1292
00:43:03,110 --> 00:43:04,140
- Don't hold it.
- Is it okay?

1293
00:43:04,640 --> 00:43:06,279
That's good. We'll make it.

1294
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:07,480
- Save it.
- Save it.

1295
00:43:07,610 --> 00:43:09,039
(The ball flew up above the head again.)

1296
00:43:09,040 --> 00:43:11,949
- Receive it and pass it.
- Receive it.

1297
00:43:11,950 --> 00:43:13,420
- Pass the ball.
- Now kick it.

1298
00:43:13,650 --> 00:43:15,049
(DinDin receives the ball by heading it.)

1299
00:43:15,050 --> 00:43:16,689
(And then Jong Min receives it with his foot.)

1300
00:43:16,690 --> 00:43:18,389
- Pass it.
- Kick it! Joon!

1301
00:43:18,390 --> 00:43:19,390
(He makes a passing mistake again.)

1302
00:43:19,560 --> 00:43:21,190
(The ball is flying toward Jong Min, not toward Joon.)

1303
00:43:21,620 --> 00:43:23,229
(Oh, no.)

1304
00:43:23,230 --> 00:43:25,530
(We'll make it if only Joon kicks it.)

1305
00:43:25,830 --> 00:43:27,330
(We must keep the ball in the air.)

1306
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:29,060
(How will it pan out?)

1307
00:43:29,130 --> 00:43:31,430
- Joon! Go for it!
- Kick it!

1308
00:43:33,500 --> 00:43:34,599
- Kick it!
- Yes!

1309
00:43:34,600 --> 00:43:36,340
(Everyone kicked the ball including the last player Joon.)

1310
00:43:36,470 --> 00:43:38,940
- Okay!
- We did it!

1311
00:43:39,780 --> 00:43:42,040
(We will have some food for dinner.)

1312
00:43:45,950 --> 00:43:48,920
- Jong Min, you were awesome.
- I saved the ball.

1313
00:43:49,250 --> 00:43:50,289
- Jong Min did a great job.
- Hey.

1314
00:43:50,290 --> 00:43:51,519
Who kicked the ball after I headed it?

1315
00:43:51,520 --> 00:43:52,859
- Jong Min kicked it.
- Who was it?

1316
00:43:52,860 --> 00:43:54,160
I see. Great job, Jong Min.

1317
00:43:54,290 --> 00:43:55,290
Nice.

1318
00:43:55,291 --> 00:43:56,460
Jong Min really did a great job at saving the ball.

1319
00:43:56,560 --> 00:43:59,060
- All right. Everyone.
- We did it.

1320
00:43:59,190 --> 00:44:00,760
You succeeded in gaining kimchi.

1321
00:44:01,600 --> 00:44:04,199
- That was a good strategy.
- It was a good idea.

1322
00:44:04,200 --> 00:44:05,899
- It was his idea.
- Joon did a good job.

1323
00:44:05,900 --> 00:44:08,670
- Let's move on to the next round.
- That was amazing.

1324
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:10,370
The third food is...

1325
00:44:10,470 --> 00:44:13,439
the fish that is in season. We can have it only in winter.

1326
00:44:13,440 --> 00:44:15,909
- It's Japanese sandfish with roe.
- That's fascinating.

1327
00:44:15,910 --> 00:44:16,979
It's really tasty.

1328
00:44:16,980 --> 00:44:20,650
The game you'll play this time is Drive a Nail Together.

1329
00:44:21,120 --> 00:44:22,380
I guess we have to do it in one go.

1330
00:44:23,450 --> 00:44:27,189
Each of the seven of you hits the nail with a hammer once.

1331
00:44:27,190 --> 00:44:28,959
If the nail goes all the way in, you'll succeed.

1332
00:44:28,960 --> 00:44:30,059
Just one nail?

1333
00:44:30,060 --> 00:44:31,459
Who's good at it? I'm good at it.

1334
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:33,899
- I'm good at it too.
- The skillful ones stand here.

1335
00:44:33,900 --> 00:44:35,659
- The weaker ones go over there.
- The four of us...

1336
00:44:35,660 --> 00:44:36,929
We need a strategy.

1337
00:44:36,930 --> 00:44:39,199
We'll give you only one chance.

1338
00:44:39,200 --> 00:44:40,969
One of us may drive it with one hit.

1339
00:44:40,970 --> 00:44:42,600
The first player should start off well.

1340
00:44:43,670 --> 00:44:44,769
- I'm not bad at it.
- Okay.

1341
00:44:44,770 --> 00:44:46,509
- But you said you were good at it.
- Yes.

1342
00:44:46,510 --> 00:44:48,639
- Will you go first?
- Okay. I'll do that.

1343
00:44:48,640 --> 00:44:50,709
- Shall I go last?
- Yes. You finish up.

1344
00:44:50,710 --> 00:44:51,749
- I'll finish up.
- He's strong.

1345
00:44:51,750 --> 00:44:53,749
- I'll go last and hit it hard.
- Good.

1346
00:44:53,750 --> 00:44:56,850
(The game requires aiming accuracy and strength.)

1347
00:44:57,190 --> 00:45:02,160
(Could the members gain Japanese sandfish with roe?)

1348
00:45:02,290 --> 00:45:03,629
- All right. We'll start.
- Here we go.

1349
00:45:03,630 --> 00:45:04,989
- We have only 1 chance.
- We have only 1 chance.

1350
00:45:04,990 --> 00:45:06,499
- Let's do this.
- Let's go!

1351
00:45:06,500 --> 00:45:08,029
- Please. We must eat it.
- I want to eat the fish.

1352
00:45:08,030 --> 00:45:09,329
One-third would be enough.

1353
00:45:09,330 --> 00:45:10,699
- Just don't make it bend...
- Oh, gosh.

1354
00:45:10,700 --> 00:45:12,169
(Please be quiet.)

1355
00:45:12,170 --> 00:45:13,440
Hey, he's older than you.

1356
00:45:13,770 --> 00:45:15,070
- I apologize on his behalf.
- That's okay.

1357
00:45:15,700 --> 00:45:18,040
(DinDin's high-level concentration made even Jong Min quiet.)

1358
00:45:18,270 --> 00:45:20,280
(How well will DinDin drive the nail?)

1359
00:45:22,410 --> 00:45:23,410
(He missed the target.)

1360
00:45:23,411 --> 00:45:25,409
- That wasn't bad.
- I was distracted.

1361
00:45:25,410 --> 00:45:27,179
- I'll go next.
- Why did you hit there?

1362
00:45:27,180 --> 00:45:28,350
You should've kept your eyes on the nail...

1363
00:45:28,920 --> 00:45:29,990
This is a good position for me.

1364
00:45:30,220 --> 00:45:31,689
I prefer to sit on the side rather than in front of it.

1365
00:45:31,690 --> 00:45:33,259
- We need it to go in.
- Boom, this isn't a practice round.

1366
00:45:33,260 --> 00:45:34,889
- Is touching it allowed?
- Yes.

1367
00:45:34,890 --> 00:45:36,160
Shouldn't you hit it in this direction?

1368
00:45:36,430 --> 00:45:37,889
- Shouldn't you hit it like this?
- Keep your eyes on the nail.

1369
00:45:37,890 --> 00:45:38,930
It's slightly tilted in this direction.

1370
00:45:39,230 --> 00:45:40,460
Keep your eyes on the nail to the last moment.

1371
00:45:41,460 --> 00:45:43,530
- It didn't touch the nail.
- You're supposed to hit the nail!

1372
00:45:44,470 --> 00:45:46,900
(He couldn't even touch the nail.)

1373
00:45:47,400 --> 00:45:51,409
(The lousy construction site director)

1374
00:45:51,410 --> 00:45:54,079
- The hammer didn't touch the nail.
- It's like he didn't kick the ball.

1375
00:45:54,080 --> 00:45:56,179
If it were golf, this would be a practice swing.

1376
00:45:56,180 --> 00:45:58,879
- I'll pretend you didn't hear it.
- Okay. It didn't touch the nail.

1377
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:00,379
From now on, if you miss the nail, that's it.

1378
00:46:00,380 --> 00:46:01,719
- That's a failed attempt.
- Oh, I see.

1379
00:46:01,720 --> 00:46:03,249
Practice a little bit before you start.

1380
00:46:03,250 --> 00:46:04,889
- Why are you so bad at it?
- I'll start now.

1381
00:46:04,890 --> 00:46:06,189
- Practice before you start. What?
- If you practice too much...

1382
00:46:06,190 --> 00:46:07,190
Darn it.

1383
00:46:07,191 --> 00:46:08,260
- I'll start now.
- Practice...

1384
00:46:08,460 --> 00:46:10,730
(He hit the edge of the nail.)

1385
00:46:10,830 --> 00:46:13,029
- Why did he hit the edge?
- It's hard to hit it straight.

1386
00:46:13,030 --> 00:46:14,030
(He walks away bitterly.)

1387
00:46:14,031 --> 00:46:15,259
- I want to eat Japanese sandfish.
- Hey.

1388
00:46:15,260 --> 00:46:16,899
- You should hit it with confidence.
- I don't think I can do it.

1389
00:46:16,900 --> 00:46:18,529
- No. Gather your confidence.
- Right. Be confident.

1390
00:46:18,530 --> 00:46:19,600
We're done for.

1391
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:21,470
What do we get if we succeed? Japanese sandfish? Gosh.

1392
00:46:21,900 --> 00:46:22,939
- Hit it with confidence.
- Okay. I'll do that.

1393
00:46:22,940 --> 00:46:24,009
- Even if it bends. It should go in.
- We need it to go in.

1394
00:46:24,010 --> 00:46:25,169
Don't hit it too hard.

1395
00:46:25,170 --> 00:46:26,210
We need it to go in. Gosh.

1396
00:46:26,310 --> 00:46:28,010
- You should do it with confidence.
- He's right.

1397
00:46:28,310 --> 00:46:29,379
- You should hit it how.
- Do it your way.

1398
00:46:29,380 --> 00:46:30,510
You should hit it now.

1399
00:46:31,380 --> 00:46:33,550
- It didn't even touch the nail.
- He hit the wrong spot.

1400
00:46:34,480 --> 00:46:35,749
He hit the wrong spot.

1401
00:46:35,750 --> 00:46:38,149
He didn't hit the nail. Couldn't you see the nail?

1402
00:46:38,150 --> 00:46:39,419
- Who's up next?
- That was funny.

1403
00:46:39,420 --> 00:46:40,560
Are you up next?

1404
00:46:40,960 --> 00:46:43,289
- Hit it with confidence.
- Hey, Jae Won.

1405
00:46:43,290 --> 00:46:44,389
- You should hit it with confidence.
- That's good.

1406
00:46:44,390 --> 00:46:45,459
Practice once.

1407
00:46:45,460 --> 00:46:48,260
(Somebody has to do a good job at this point.)

1408
00:46:49,260 --> 00:46:50,429
Yes, that's good. Okay. Let's go.

1409
00:46:50,430 --> 00:46:51,499
- Hit it just like that.
- I'll start.

1410
00:46:51,500 --> 00:46:52,500
(Could they overcome this crisis?)

1411
00:46:52,501 --> 00:46:53,540
- You've got this.
- Go for it.

1412
00:46:53,940 --> 00:46:55,270
- I'll hit it hard.
- Go for it.

1413
00:46:56,640 --> 00:46:59,310
(He hit it!)

1414
00:46:59,740 --> 00:47:01,509
(How well did Jae Won hammer the nail?)

1415
00:47:01,510 --> 00:47:02,950
- It went in quite deeply.
- That was good.

1416
00:47:03,180 --> 00:47:04,480
- I'll hit it hard.
- Go for it.

1417
00:47:06,010 --> 00:47:07,479
(He put it in deeply!)

1418
00:47:07,480 --> 00:47:08,920
- It went in quite deeply.
- That was good.

1419
00:47:13,020 --> 00:47:16,560
(He hit in the wrong spot, but the nail went in.)

1420
00:47:17,160 --> 00:47:20,800
(Anyway, Jae Won got it done well.)

1421
00:47:20,830 --> 00:47:21,859
- Who's up next? You?
- Yes.

1422
00:47:21,860 --> 00:47:23,269
- Two members are left now.
- I'll put in half of it.

1423
00:47:23,270 --> 00:47:24,869
- Can you do that?
- You should put in half of it.

1424
00:47:24,870 --> 00:47:26,439
- Only then can Se Yoon pull it off.
- Jong Min, practice first.

1425
00:47:26,440 --> 00:47:27,469
- Won't you practice first?
- You should put in half of it.

1426
00:47:27,470 --> 00:47:29,709
- Aim well and hit it straight.
- You should put in half of it.

1427
00:47:29,710 --> 00:47:30,740
(You can do it.)

1428
00:47:31,670 --> 00:47:32,740
- Okay. He did it.
- Oh, my.

1429
00:47:35,010 --> 00:47:37,249
(While practicing, he hit it nonchalantly!)

1430
00:47:37,250 --> 00:47:38,409
- What just happened?
- He did a great job.

1431
00:47:38,410 --> 00:47:40,549
- That's a good method.
- You're surprised too, right?

1432
00:47:40,550 --> 00:47:43,049
- Let's go. Let's cheer for him.
- Wait for a second.

1433
00:47:43,050 --> 00:47:44,920
(The nail went in noticeably deeply as they did unexpectedly well.)

1434
00:47:45,150 --> 00:47:47,660
(There's only one person left now.)

1435
00:47:47,690 --> 00:47:49,059
Hit it hard! Please.

1436
00:47:49,060 --> 00:47:51,490
(Se Yoon, the strongest member of 2 Days 1 Night)

1437
00:47:51,760 --> 00:47:54,460
(While all the other members hope for his success,)

1438
00:47:54,700 --> 00:47:57,070
(will Se Yoon succeed?)

1439
00:47:59,100 --> 00:48:01,570
(He hit it!)

1440
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:04,140
(What will be the result?)

1441
00:48:05,270 --> 00:48:07,610
(Only this much is left.)

1442
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:10,449
(That was close.)

1443
00:48:10,450 --> 00:48:11,579
- It went inside.
- It went inside.

1444
00:48:11,580 --> 00:48:13,120
This is how we do it at home.

1445
00:48:13,350 --> 00:48:14,649
- We do it like this at home.
- We do it like this.

1446
00:48:14,650 --> 00:48:16,489
We can hang a frame. We need to hang a frame.

1447
00:48:16,490 --> 00:48:17,820
We need this much to hang a frame.

1448
00:48:17,920 --> 00:48:19,990
Unfortunately, you failed!

1449
00:48:20,820 --> 00:48:21,820
It doesn't hit so well.

1450
00:48:21,821 --> 00:48:23,059
Where are you hitting?

1451
00:48:23,060 --> 00:48:24,489
(They failed.)

1452
00:48:24,490 --> 00:48:25,859
I should have done it.

1453
00:48:25,860 --> 00:48:28,060
- I should have done it at first.
- This...

1454
00:48:28,800 --> 00:48:29,929
Do we only get rice?

1455
00:48:29,930 --> 00:48:31,670
We don't even have rice now.

1456
00:48:31,800 --> 00:48:33,600
You have kimchi.

1457
00:48:33,770 --> 00:48:36,470
- Really?
- We had potatoes for lunch.

1458
00:48:36,540 --> 00:48:37,640
What is it this time?

1459
00:48:38,340 --> 00:48:39,710
The fourth food...

1460
00:48:39,810 --> 00:48:43,149
is a cold-weather soul food that comes to mind on freezing days.

1461
00:48:43,150 --> 00:48:44,779
- It's ramyeon.
- It's ramyeon.

1462
00:48:44,780 --> 00:48:46,380
- Two per person.
- We definitely need to get this.

1463
00:48:46,920 --> 00:48:49,479
(Ramyeon tastes even better in cold days.)

1464
00:48:49,480 --> 00:48:51,089
- How many?
- How many?

1465
00:48:51,090 --> 00:48:52,449
- Please bring it in.
- We at least need seven.

1466
00:48:52,450 --> 00:48:53,989
What? How many are those?

1467
00:48:53,990 --> 00:48:55,420
- Five?
- Five?

1468
00:48:57,760 --> 00:48:59,089
- What?
- What's wrong with you?

1469
00:48:59,090 --> 00:49:00,960
Do 7 people normally share 5 packets of ramyeon?

1470
00:49:01,530 --> 00:49:03,069
Do you eat like that?

1471
00:49:03,070 --> 00:49:04,930
I can eat five alone if I'm in good condition.

1472
00:49:05,200 --> 00:49:07,039
If we share that among seven people,

1473
00:49:07,040 --> 00:49:09,099
we'll only get this much like the noodles at a wedding.

1474
00:49:09,100 --> 00:49:10,540
- Right.
- Only this much.

1475
00:49:11,340 --> 00:49:13,039
- One per person.
- Okay.

1476
00:49:13,040 --> 00:49:14,709
- One per person.
- Okay.

1477
00:49:14,710 --> 00:49:16,479
- One per person.
- You just placed five there?

1478
00:49:16,480 --> 00:49:18,449
You should have told us earlier.

1479
00:49:18,450 --> 00:49:19,649
Please.

1480
00:49:19,650 --> 00:49:20,679
I'm sorry.

1481
00:49:20,680 --> 00:49:21,950
(They apologize quickly.)

1482
00:49:22,220 --> 00:49:23,289
- This time...
- Yes.

1483
00:49:23,290 --> 00:49:24,290
(Ramyeon is at stake in this round.)

1484
00:49:24,315 --> 00:49:26,085
It's Breaking Chopsticks with the Butt.

1485
00:49:26,720 --> 00:49:28,690
- Okay.
- Se Yoon is good at this.

1486
00:49:28,890 --> 00:49:31,960
(Wooden chopsticks are tied together.)

1487
00:49:32,190 --> 00:49:37,030
