01:05:26,945 --> 01:05:28,844
(Chef Noodle-eater Jong Min's chewy ramyeon is ready.)

1996
01:05:28,845 --> 01:05:31,145
I'll distribute the noodles. Please distribute the soup.

1997
01:05:31,715 --> 01:05:32,945
Okay.

1998
01:05:33,285 --> 01:05:35,244
- One by one.
- Take a bowl of ramyeon.

1999
01:05:35,245 --> 01:05:37,554
- Here.
- Bring your seats.

2000
01:05:37,555 --> 01:05:39,224
- Here.
- Here you go.

2001
01:05:39,225 --> 01:05:40,884
Take this. Hold on.

2002
01:05:40,885 --> 01:05:42,795
This is the wild.

2003
01:05:43,055 --> 01:05:45,355
It's my first time eating like this.

2004
01:05:45,855 --> 01:05:46,964
Thank you for the food!

2005
01:05:46,965 --> 01:05:48,324
The wild!

2006
01:05:48,325 --> 01:05:49,765
- The wild!
- The wild!

2007
01:05:49,795 --> 01:05:51,565
- 2 Days!
- 1 Night!

2008
01:05:53,035 --> 01:05:57,705
(Jae Won drinks the warm soup first.)

2009
01:05:59,205 --> 01:06:00,445
What kind of ramyeon...

2010
01:06:01,445 --> 01:06:03,375
(The chewy noodles fill his mouth.)

2011
01:06:03,775 --> 01:06:07,415
(The taste of the wild keeps going in.)

2012
01:06:07,515 --> 01:06:09,014
It's going to be very chewy.

2013
01:06:09,015 --> 01:06:10,275
How is it, Jae Won?

2014
01:06:10,385 --> 01:06:11,414
It's really good.

2015
01:06:11,415 --> 01:06:12,455
It's amazing.

2016
01:06:12,625 --> 01:06:14,825
It's the best ramyeon I've ever had. I mean it.

2017
01:06:15,491 --> 01:06:17,231
(Feeling proud)

2018
01:06:17,295 --> 01:06:19,525
This is your next meal after the potatoes.

2019
01:06:19,625 --> 01:06:21,024
That's right. This is practically my first meal.

2020
01:06:21,025 --> 01:06:23,065
- Right.
- It's really touching.

2021
01:06:23,495 --> 01:06:25,294
(Boom also enjoys the ramyeon...)

2022
01:06:25,295 --> 01:06:26,404
It makes no sense.

2023
01:06:26,405 --> 01:06:28,804
There's more ramyeon. Get more if you want.

2024
01:06:28,805 --> 01:06:30,305
- Okay.
- They'll get soggy.

2025
01:06:30,405 --> 01:06:31,434
Okay.

2026
01:06:31,435 --> 01:06:33,875
(after grilling the meat.)

2027
01:06:34,175 --> 01:06:39,915
(Even Joon, who kept looking for ramyeon. is eating well.)

2028
01:06:41,115 --> 01:06:43,815
(A puff of breath is coming from the side.)

2029
01:06:44,785 --> 01:06:47,825
I guess it's really cold. You can see your breath.

2030
01:06:47,955 --> 01:06:48,984
(It's so cold.)

2031
01:06:48,985 --> 01:06:50,295
It's so cold.

2032
01:06:51,425 --> 01:06:52,454
(It's feeling like minus 20°C.)

2033
01:06:52,455 --> 01:06:53,895
I feel cold but warm as well.

2034
01:06:54,525 --> 01:06:56,165
Try the meat. It's amazing.

2035
01:06:56,695 --> 01:06:58,535
Get a bunch of meat.

2036
01:06:58,665 --> 01:07:01,634
(I was the one who grilled it,)

2037
01:07:01,635 --> 01:07:03,474
(but it's so good.)

2038
01:07:03,475 --> 01:07:05,034
The meat is so good.

2039
01:07:05,035 --> 01:07:06,905
- It's good, isn't it?
- The meat is so good.

2040
01:07:07,505 --> 01:07:08,644
(Eating)

2041
01:07:08,645 --> 01:07:09,945
Gosh!

2042
01:07:10,775 --> 01:07:12,175
The Real Winter Training is doable!

2043
01:07:12,885 --> 01:07:14,515
- Gosh.
- The meat is good, isn't it?

2044
01:07:14,845 --> 01:07:17,515
This was also grilled over a straw fire.

2045
01:07:18,115 --> 01:07:19,884
It's the taste of trading off our house.

2046
01:07:19,885 --> 01:07:20,984
Right!

2047
01:07:20,985 --> 01:07:22,625
You can see it all.

2048
01:07:22,725 --> 01:07:24,454
You can see the fire sear into the meat.

2049
01:07:24,455 --> 01:07:25,524
It's completely smoked.

2050
01:07:25,525 --> 01:07:27,395
(The straw fire covered the meat nicely.)

2051
01:07:27,525 --> 01:07:29,594
- Gosh, just like this.
- This is happiness.

2052
01:07:29,595 --> 01:07:30,664
It should be wrapped with the ramyeon.

2053
01:07:30,665 --> 01:07:31,735
How much is this worth?

2054
01:07:34,835 --> 01:07:39,845
(One man attracts attention behind Boom's fancy noodle-eating.)

2055
01:07:40,605 --> 01:07:47,085
(Jae Won's hat slides down as his head is so small.)

2056
01:07:47,445 --> 01:07:51,285
(These two are wearing the same-size hats.)

2057
01:07:52,285 --> 01:07:59,525
(He gives up on his vision and focuses on eating.)

2058
01:07:59,625 --> 01:08:01,624
- Have you finished eating?
- Yes.

2059
01:08:01,625 --> 01:08:02,995
- Yes. Somewhat.
- Yes.

2060
01:08:03,135 --> 01:08:05,135
Well, now,

2061
01:08:05,265 --> 01:08:07,065
Boom and Jae Won...

2062
01:08:07,535 --> 01:08:08,565
What?

2063
01:08:08,835 --> 01:08:10,274
They have to leave for work.

2064
01:08:10,275 --> 01:08:11,635
- What?
- What?

2065
01:08:11,975 --> 01:08:13,444
- Forget about Boom.
- What?

2066
01:08:13,445 --> 01:08:15,275
- Can't Jae Won stay with us?
- Right.

2067
01:08:15,445 --> 01:08:17,275
(Feeling bad)

2068
01:08:17,475 --> 01:08:19,445
The things Boom showed us today...

2069
01:08:19,585 --> 01:08:20,845
will be shown again tomorrow.

2070
01:08:21,215 --> 01:08:22,714
He can go now. He showed everything he could.

2071
01:08:22,715 --> 01:08:23,715
(The entertainer showed everything he could today.)

2072
01:08:23,716 --> 01:08:25,584
Well, let me explain.

2073
01:08:25,585 --> 01:08:27,355
Next morning,

2074
01:08:27,455 --> 01:08:30,094
I have a shoot for "Stars' Top Recipe at Fun-Staurant."

2075
01:08:30,095 --> 01:08:31,194
- I see.
- Really?

2076
01:08:31,195 --> 01:08:32,354
I'm not suspecting you,

2077
01:08:32,355 --> 01:08:33,494
but can we get that checked with a KBS employee?

2078
01:08:33,495 --> 01:08:34,625
Gosh.

2079
01:08:35,095 --> 01:08:36,395
- What are you saying?
- Can we make a phone call?

2080
01:08:36,665 --> 01:08:38,164
- We already knew about it.
- Does he really have a shoot?

2081
01:08:38,165 --> 01:08:39,234
Yes.

2082
01:08:39,235 --> 01:08:40,464
I also have a shoot.

2083
01:08:40,465 --> 01:08:41,534
(These two made time for the day even within their tight schedules.)

2084
01:08:41,535 --> 01:08:43,575
Why would you go after building the house?

2085
01:08:43,905 --> 01:08:45,534
I feel really bad about having to go.

2086
01:08:45,535 --> 01:08:47,474
That was why we did our best for building the house.

2087
01:08:47,475 --> 01:08:48,674
- No wonder.
- They worked so hard.

2088
01:08:48,675 --> 01:08:49,874
He took the initiative...

2089
01:08:49,875 --> 01:08:51,444
and worked so hard along with Jae Won.

2090
01:08:51,445 --> 01:08:52,985
So that there wouldn't be a single gap for wind to come in.

2091
01:08:53,145 --> 01:08:54,615
It's just the five of us sleeping here in the end.

2092
01:08:56,585 --> 01:08:58,385
- It's a bit disappointing.
- Right.

2093
01:08:58,955 --> 01:09:01,655
Jae Won should've shown some of his impressive moments.

2094
01:09:02,055 --> 01:09:03,724
He should show them next time...

2095
01:09:03,725 --> 01:09:05,024
- when he makes a glorious return.
- Right.

2096
01:09:05,025 --> 01:09:07,324
- Right.
- I will really come back...

2097
01:09:07,325 --> 01:09:09,564
and make sure to make up...

2098
01:09:09,565 --> 01:09:11,194
for everything I made a mess of.

2099
01:09:11,195 --> 01:09:12,265
- Gosh.
- Right.

2100
01:09:12,635 --> 01:09:14,505
- Gosh.
- You did make a big mess.

2101
01:09:15,605 --> 01:09:17,475
You literally ruined everything.

2102
01:09:17,705 --> 01:09:19,645
- We just didn't bring it up.
- Why be like that?

2103
01:09:19,775 --> 01:09:21,045
When we invited them,

2104
01:09:21,305 --> 01:09:23,614
we didn't tell them about anything.

2105
01:09:23,615 --> 01:09:26,285
They didn't know what to expect at all.

2106
01:09:27,045 --> 01:09:28,644
They would've been very surprised.

2107
01:09:28,645 --> 01:09:29,655
(These two never expected it to be Real Winter Training.)

2108
01:09:30,185 --> 01:09:34,825
(They came thinking it was a winter workshop.)

2109
01:09:35,285 --> 01:09:39,355
(They unexpectedly had to face Real Winter Training.)

2110
01:09:39,765 --> 01:09:45,735
(Talking and slapstick comedy)

2111
01:09:46,335 --> 01:09:49,335
(Boom showed all of his charms as an entertainer.)

2112
01:09:49,575 --> 01:09:52,134
The Real Winter Training is the toughest challenge.

2113
01:09:52,135 --> 01:09:53,204
- Right.
- Right.

2114
01:09:53,205 --> 01:09:55,245
The fact that I survived this...

2115
01:09:55,645 --> 01:09:58,714
feels like something I can boast about as an entertainer.

2116
01:09:58,715 --> 01:10:00,214
Isn't it hard to say he survived it?

2117
01:10:00,215 --> 01:10:01,544
You're not spending the night with us.

2118
01:10:01,545 --> 01:10:02,614
Right.

2119
01:10:02,615 --> 01:10:05,314
You have to experience your mouth freezing up.

2120
01:10:05,315 --> 01:10:06,754
- I've only survived half of it.
- Right.

2121
01:10:06,755 --> 01:10:07,855
Right.

2122
01:10:08,425 --> 01:10:10,625
I really enjoyed it.

2123
01:10:11,795 --> 01:10:14,294
It felt like I came to a retreat after a while.

2124
01:10:14,295 --> 01:10:15,964
- A retreat.
- Even though things were tough,

2125
01:10:15,965 --> 01:10:18,865
there are memories that feel good later on.

2126
01:10:20,035 --> 01:10:25,175
(The variety show rookie was brought to the jungle.)

2127
01:10:25,635 --> 01:10:31,975
(He got flustered all day.)

2128
01:10:32,475 --> 01:10:39,315
(Outdoor variety show challenge for the first love actor)

2129
01:10:39,985 --> 01:10:47,625
(He showed slapstick comedy with his clumsiness.)

2130
01:10:48,595 --> 01:10:55,634
(Jae Won showed a lot of his charms including his killer cuteness.)

2131
01:10:55,635 --> 01:10:58,834
More than anything, it was great to see Se Yoon.

2132
01:10:58,835 --> 01:11:00,304
- Gosh!
- Gosh!

2133
01:11:00,305 --> 01:11:01,444
- That's great.
- He feels like...

2134
01:11:01,445 --> 01:11:02,574
an actual younger brother.

2135
01:11:02,575 --> 01:11:03,644
Gosh!

2136
01:11:03,645 --> 01:11:04,914
- The holidays.
- Okay.

2137
01:11:04,915 --> 01:11:06,645
- Visit him during the holidays.
- He looks so happy.

2138
01:11:06,685 --> 01:11:08,814
He moves to the top of younger friends!

2139
01:11:08,815 --> 01:11:10,015
Jae Won is at the top!

2140
01:11:10,185 --> 01:11:12,054
- What about Nam Joo Hyuk?
- Joo Hyuk is pushed down.

2141
01:11:12,055 --> 01:11:13,585
- Joo Hyuk is second?
- Yes.

2142
01:11:13,755 --> 01:11:14,985
Second by a big difference.

2143
01:11:15,155 --> 01:11:16,324
He moves up to the top.

2144
01:11:16,325 --> 01:11:17,355
(He becomes Se Yoon's top younger friend.)

2145
01:11:17,955 --> 01:11:20,964
It was just one day together, but it really felt like...

2146
01:11:20,965 --> 01:11:22,265
we became a family.

2147
01:11:22,525 --> 01:11:23,595
What is this?

2148
01:11:23,635 --> 01:11:29,335
(They survived through the cold together.)

2149
01:11:29,875 --> 01:11:37,345
(The seven men became a family in just a single day.)

2150
01:11:37,815 --> 01:11:39,745
The Real Winter Training Center. 2 Days,

2151
01:11:39,915 --> 01:11:41,584
- 1 Night!
- 1 Night!

2152
01:11:41,585 --> 01:11:43,114
- Yes!
- Yes!

2153
01:11:43,115 --> 01:11:44,384
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

2154
01:11:44,385 --> 01:11:46,384
- Bye!
- Bye!

2155
01:11:46,385 --> 01:11:47,454
- Good night!
- Thank you!

2156
01:11:47,455 --> 01:11:48,585
- Bye!
- Good night!

2157
01:11:49,625 --> 01:11:52,294
(The Real Winter Training night begins at minus 17°C.)

2158
01:11:52,295 --> 01:11:53,495
It's cold, isn't it, everyone?

2159
01:11:53,965 --> 01:11:56,435
Let's head inside for a while.

2160
01:11:58,435 --> 01:12:00,764
(At the base camp in Inje, Gangwon Province,)

2161
01:12:00,765 --> 01:12:03,905
(there is just one indoor area.)

2162
01:12:04,705 --> 01:12:06,134
- What?
- What?

2163
01:12:06,135 --> 01:12:07,605
- What is this place?
- There was a place indoors!

2164
01:12:08,175 --> 01:12:10,114
There's a room like this deep in the mountains?

2165
01:12:10,115 --> 01:12:11,215
You said there wasn't a place like this!

2166
01:12:11,775 --> 01:12:13,185
Coming in.

2167
01:12:13,815 --> 01:12:14,914
- What?
- What?

2168
01:12:14,915 --> 01:12:16,044
There was a place to stay in!

2169
01:12:16,045 --> 01:12:17,384
(The warm rooms fight against the weather of minus 17°C...)

2170
01:12:17,385 --> 01:12:18,715
(with the heating system.)

2171
01:12:19,055 --> 01:12:21,325
(After being out in the wild for 8 hours...)

2172
01:12:21,425 --> 01:12:22,725
This is my room!

2173
01:12:22,885 --> 01:12:24,155
- What?
- This place is amazing.

2174
01:12:24,555 --> 01:12:25,695
What?

2175
01:12:26,425 --> 01:12:28,065
There was a place this warm around here!

2176
01:12:28,265 --> 01:12:31,035
Why leave us outside with a great place like this?

2177
01:12:31,065 --> 01:12:32,394
- No way!
- What?

2178
01:12:32,395 --> 01:12:34,105
This is my room!

2179
01:12:34,365 --> 01:12:35,435
Okay!

2180
01:12:35,935 --> 01:12:37,104
- Okay!
- What is this?

2181
01:12:37,105 --> 01:12:38,375
- What's going on?
- The time has come!

2182
01:12:38,905 --> 01:12:40,075
This is driving me crazy.

2183
01:12:41,045 --> 01:12:42,244
- What?
- One person will be saved?

2184
01:12:42,245 --> 01:12:44,115
It's the first and last opportunity.

2185
01:12:44,475 --> 01:12:46,617
The chance to avoid sleeping outdoors...

2186
01:12:46,915 --> 01:12:48,145
during the Real Winter Training...

2187
01:12:49,015 --> 01:12:50,384
will be given to just one person.

2188
01:12:50,385 --> 01:12:51,854
- One person?
- Just one person.

2189
01:12:51,855 --> 01:12:53,585
(Just one person can sleep indoors.)

2190
01:12:53,685 --> 01:12:55,424
Being able to sleep here would be...

2191
01:12:55,425 --> 01:12:56,554
(Only 1 person can survive.)

2192
01:12:56,555 --> 01:12:58,324
Being able to sleep here would be amazing.

2193
01:12:58,325 --> 01:12:59,325
What is this?

2194
01:12:59,326 --> 01:13:01,194
DinDin slept indoors last year!

2195
01:13:01,195 --> 01:13:02,624
It would be amazing if you sleep indoors again.

2196
01:13:02,625 --> 01:13:03,934
Don't you have any thoughts about giving up?

2197
01:13:03,935 --> 01:13:04,935
- You slept indoors last year.
- Of course, I don't!

2198
01:13:04,936 --> 01:13:05,965
What are you saying?

2199
01:13:06,335 --> 01:13:10,405
(After making the worst house,)

2200
01:13:10,835 --> 01:13:13,244
(DinDin slept indoors alone.)

2201
01:13:13,245 --> 01:13:15,105
I'm not sure if I can do this.

2202
01:13:15,805 --> 01:13:17,714
What is this about?

2203
01:13:17,715 --> 01:13:18,945
All right, everyone.

2204
01:13:19,445 --> 01:13:22,714
- The game for the one winner...
- Please!

2205
01:13:22,715 --> 01:13:23,954
- who will sleep here...
- What is it?

2206
01:13:23,955 --> 01:13:25,855
- Please!
- It must be a game of luck.

2207
01:13:26,755 --> 01:13:28,325
It's Round and Round.

2208
01:13:28,385 --> 01:13:29,725
- What is that?
- Is it a game of luck?

2209
01:13:29,895 --> 01:13:31,054
- Round and Round.
- It's not a game of luck.

2210
01:13:31,055 --> 01:13:32,494
- It should be a game of luck.
- Isn't that a game of strength?

2211
01:13:32,495 --> 01:13:33,725
Let's play a game of luck.

2212
01:13:33,965 --> 01:13:36,635
While dancing to "Round and Round..."

2213
01:13:36,865 --> 01:13:38,334
(Round and Round)

2214
01:13:38,335 --> 01:13:42,635
(The members dance excitedly while "Round and Round" plays.)

2215
01:13:42,735 --> 01:13:44,135
When the song stops,

2216
01:13:44,975 --> 01:13:47,745
you have to enter each room based on the right number of people.

2217
01:13:47,805 --> 01:13:49,075
There are two rooms.

2218
01:13:49,505 --> 01:13:51,445
(There are 2 rooms.)

2219
01:13:51,515 --> 01:13:53,415
The fixed number of people...

2220
01:13:54,215 --> 01:13:55,844
can be checked only after you enter the room.

2221
01:13:55,845 --> 01:13:57,214
- I get it.
- It's a game of luck.

2222
01:13:57,215 --> 01:13:59,054
After going into a room after dancing...

2223
01:13:59,055 --> 01:14:00,184
- Let's say it's the 2 of us.
- Let's say it's the 2 of us.

2224
01:14:00,185 --> 01:14:01,254
- We both went in.
- We both went in.

2225
01:14:01,255 --> 01:14:02,524
- It says 1.
- But it says 1.

2226
01:14:02,525 --> 01:14:03,955
That means one person must leave.

2227
01:14:04,125 --> 01:14:05,224
- Right.
- Right.

2228
01:14:05,225 --> 01:14:07,495
- Let's not put in our fingers.
- That can't happen.

2229
01:14:07,565 --> 01:14:09,995
- Let's play it fair.
- All right. Let's give it a try.

2230
01:14:10,435 --> 01:14:12,394
This is a complete game of luck.

2231
01:14:12,395 --> 01:14:13,935
- It's based on luck.
- Right.

2232
01:14:14,305 --> 01:14:16,835
You survive if you enter the room with the right number of people.

2233
01:14:17,281 --> 01:14:18,418
If you fail,

2234
01:14:18,775 --> 01:14:20,744
you will get sent out to the Real Winter Training Center...

2235
01:14:20,745 --> 01:14:21,905
right away.

2236
01:14:23,515 --> 01:14:26,145
(Current temperature: Minus 17°C)

2237
01:14:26,275 --> 01:14:27,844
Take your blindfolds.

2238
01:14:27,845 --> 01:14:29,584
(What will happen to the members?)

2239
01:14:29,585 --> 01:14:30,985
- Everyone.
- Let's go.

2240
01:14:31,015 --> 01:14:32,084
(They put on blindfolds for a fair game.)

2241
01:14:32,085 --> 01:14:33,555
I can't see anything at all.

2242
01:14:34,355 --> 01:14:36,254
- Round and Round - I'll put yours on for you.

2243
01:14:36,255 --> 01:14:37,794
There can be a lot of cheating.

2244
01:14:37,795 --> 01:14:39,654
- Here.
- Who would cheat?

2245
