My goodness.

2498
01:24:45,135 --> 01:24:46,835
It feels so strange.

2499
01:24:47,905 --> 01:24:51,675
(And one person who will feel really strange)

2500
01:24:59,875 --> 01:25:01,484
(Please go out.)

2501
01:25:01,485 --> 01:25:03,245
(Laughing)

2502
01:25:04,155 --> 01:25:08,085
(Se Yoon is out.)

2503
01:25:09,625 --> 01:25:12,255
(He checks the note again.)

2504
01:25:13,965 --> 01:25:14,965
What...

2505
01:25:15,665 --> 01:25:20,605
(It was a vain dream on a midwinter night.)

2506
01:25:23,705 --> 01:25:25,704
(Tonight's indoor sleeper appears.)

2507
01:25:25,705 --> 01:25:26,774
I told you so.

2508
01:25:26,775 --> 01:25:27,945
- Joon!
- All right.

2509
01:25:28,205 --> 01:25:29,945
- Lee Joon!
- It was this room.

2510
01:25:29,975 --> 01:25:31,945
It feels so unreal that I don't know what to say.

2511
01:25:32,915 --> 01:25:34,214
I can't believe this.

2512
01:25:34,215 --> 01:25:38,155
(This should've been my room.)

2513
01:25:38,255 --> 01:25:39,484
We told you to switch.

2514
01:25:39,485 --> 01:25:41,085
That's the room where you fell.

2515
01:25:41,185 --> 01:25:42,424
We told you to go to the room...

2516
01:25:42,425 --> 01:25:44,054
- where you fell.
- I can't believe this.

2517
01:25:44,055 --> 01:25:45,755
I told you to go there.

2518
01:25:46,155 --> 01:25:47,325
Oh, dear.

2519
01:25:51,595 --> 01:25:55,835
(Se Yoon just kept crying like that for a long time.)

2520
01:25:56,114 --> 01:25:58,384
Lee Joon sleeps indoors.

2521
01:25:58,905 --> 01:26:00,844
You may take a hot shower and go to sleep now.

2522
01:26:00,845 --> 01:26:02,605
This is crazy. It's been a long time.

2523
01:26:02,775 --> 01:26:03,945
Se Yoon.

2524
01:26:05,015 --> 01:26:06,145
Please go out.

2525
01:26:07,715 --> 01:26:09,215
Please come on out.

2526
01:26:09,345 --> 01:26:11,184
The last rule of 2 Days 1 Night.

2527
01:26:11,185 --> 01:26:12,684
They will come to get it.

2528
01:26:12,685 --> 01:26:14,784
- Okay.
- Switch when you can switch.

2529
01:26:14,785 --> 01:26:16,084
(The rule of 2 Days 1 Night: Switch when you can switch.)

2530
01:26:16,085 --> 01:26:17,654
I told you to switch.

2531
01:26:17,655 --> 01:26:18,724
(Se Yoon leaves like that.)

2532
01:26:18,725 --> 01:26:19,529
Joon.

2533
01:26:20,965 --> 01:26:21,995
Goodnight.

2534
01:26:22,065 --> 01:26:24,394
I was so happy...

2535
01:26:24,395 --> 01:26:25,565
that I couldn't say anything.

2536
01:26:25,835 --> 01:26:26,995
I was just like this.

2537
01:26:29,305 --> 01:26:32,535
(He gets emotional while putting on his shoes.)

2538
01:26:32,775 --> 01:26:34,745
I had a very happy dream.

2539
01:26:35,975 --> 01:26:38,214
All right. We should sleep here since we've built the house.

2540
01:26:38,215 --> 01:26:40,014
(The losers are back to the Real Winter Training Center.)

2541
01:26:40,015 --> 01:26:41,615
It's really cold today.

2542
01:26:42,485 --> 01:26:43,614
What's the temperature?

2543
01:26:43,615 --> 01:26:46,655
(The current temperature is minus 17°C.)

2544
01:26:47,485 --> 01:26:49,324
Nothing has changed since this time last year.

2545
01:26:49,325 --> 01:26:50,385
(This scene feels like deja vu.)

2546
01:26:50,595 --> 01:26:52,555
Even the chair is frozen.

2547
01:26:53,455 --> 01:26:55,895
What's this? Hey, look at this. It got wet with dew.

2548
01:26:56,565 --> 01:26:57,664
It's covered with dew.

2549
01:26:57,665 --> 01:26:58,695
(In the coldest weather ever, even the chair is frozen.)

2550
01:26:58,995 --> 01:27:00,964
Here's a Real Winter gift.

2551
01:27:00,965 --> 01:27:02,135
(Consolation gifts for the outdoor sleepers)

2552
01:27:02,665 --> 01:27:05,705
(Sweet potatoes are perfect real winter snacks.)

2553
01:27:07,005 --> 01:27:08,405
Lee Joon!

2554
01:27:09,345 --> 01:27:10,814
His eyes met mine.

2555
01:27:10,815 --> 01:27:12,614
(Playing cameraman instead of sleeping)

2556
01:27:12,615 --> 01:27:14,215
Strike a pose, please.

2557
01:27:14,315 --> 01:27:15,415
Make a finger heart.

2558
01:27:16,185 --> 01:27:18,084
(This heart... feels off.)

2559
01:27:18,085 --> 01:27:19,185
Joon.

2560
01:27:19,785 --> 01:27:20,824
I like that.

2561
01:27:20,825 --> 01:27:22,385
An ending pose. That's it.

2562
01:27:23,385 --> 01:27:24,954
(Switching targets)

2563
01:27:24,955 --> 01:27:27,194
Se Yoon, strike an ending pose.

2564
01:27:27,195 --> 01:27:29,724
(Joon's camera)

2565
01:27:29,725 --> 01:27:30,994
(The closing fairy's tooth flirt)

2566
01:27:30,995 --> 01:27:32,935
I can't get it all in the frame.

2567
01:27:33,435 --> 01:27:35,335
You're good. True entertainers.

2568
01:27:36,365 --> 01:27:38,835
(Reality hits)

2569
01:27:39,905 --> 01:27:40,974
Look at my breath.

2570
01:27:40,975 --> 01:27:42,604
(It's so cold, their breath looks like steam.)

2571
01:27:42,605 --> 01:27:44,015
My hands feel numb.

2572
01:27:45,145 --> 01:27:47,444
- Darn it.
- What are you doing?

2573
01:27:47,445 --> 01:27:48,914
(And they must sleep in this cold.)

2574
01:27:48,915 --> 01:27:50,385
I feel so sorry for them.

2575
01:27:52,355 --> 01:27:53,296
I'm concerned.

2576
01:27:53,455 --> 01:27:55,184
(With a face...)

2577
01:27:55,185 --> 01:27:56,284
They'll manage.

2578
01:27:56,285 --> 01:27:57,455
(of zero concern,)

2579
01:27:57,480 --> 01:28:01,650
(Joon goes back indoors to sleep.)

2580
01:28:01,995 --> 01:28:03,324
Let's stare at the fire.

2581
01:28:03,325 --> 01:28:05,464
(They gaze at the flames...)

2582
01:28:05,465 --> 01:28:06,734
Listen to the crackling sound.

2583
01:28:06,735 --> 01:28:08,435
(while the sweet potatoes cook.)

2584
01:28:09,635 --> 01:28:12,404
(They are hungry,)

2585
01:28:12,405 --> 01:28:16,105
(but the warmth makes them sleepy.)

2586
01:28:16,375 --> 01:28:18,445
Can't we poke it with this? Did that work?

2587
01:28:19,475 --> 01:28:21,915
(A charcoal sweet potato)

2588
01:28:22,085 --> 01:28:23,715
That's plain charcoal.

2589
01:28:24,255 --> 01:28:25,514
You can't eat that.

2590
01:28:25,515 --> 01:28:26,585
Charcoal-flavored sweet potatoes.

2591
01:28:26,855 --> 01:28:29,184
(The charcoal sweet potato is still on fire.)

2592
01:28:29,185 --> 01:28:30,225
It's out?

2593
01:28:30,695 --> 01:28:32,725
(He takes a bite.)

2594
01:28:35,325 --> 01:28:37,865
(So hot)

2595
01:28:38,395 --> 01:28:39,564
(It looks terrible...)

2596
01:28:39,565 --> 01:28:40,865
It's really sweet.

2597
01:28:41,265 --> 01:28:42,304
So sweet.

2598
01:28:42,305 --> 01:28:43,975
(but it tastes awesome.)

2599
01:28:44,405 --> 01:28:48,174
(Jong Min picks up a different sweet potato.)

2600
01:28:48,175 --> 01:28:49,245
Let's eat.

2601
01:28:50,075 --> 01:28:51,214
(This one isn't charcoal.)

2602
01:28:51,215 --> 01:28:52,245
What's wrong?

2603
01:28:52,615 --> 01:28:53,645
Gosh!

2604
01:28:57,555 --> 01:28:59,785
(What's he doing?)

2605
01:29:01,355 --> 01:29:04,324
(After a great struggle, he breaks the sweet potato.)

2606
01:29:04,325 --> 01:29:06,295
Goodness. Take a huge bite.

2607
01:29:06,807 --> 01:29:07,568
A big one.

2608
01:29:09,395 --> 01:29:11,164
- Gosh!
- A big one.

2609
01:29:11,165 --> 01:29:13,865
(Crunch)

2610
01:29:14,105 --> 01:29:15,504
- Gosh.
- How does it taste?

2611
01:29:15,505 --> 01:29:17,835
It's like eating sweet potato-flavored kkakdugi.

2612
01:29:19,405 --> 01:29:21,205
It's raw in the center...

2613
01:29:21,705 --> 01:29:22,974
and warm on the outside.

2614
01:29:22,975 --> 01:29:24,744
- It's half-cooked.
- It's half-cooked.

2615
01:29:24,745 --> 01:29:26,145
- A half-cooked sweet potato.
- It's half-cooked.

2616
01:29:26,275 --> 01:29:28,145
- It still tastes good.
- It tastes good.

2617
01:29:28,545 --> 01:29:29,615
It's sweet.

2618
01:29:30,185 --> 01:29:31,099
Sweet as honey.

2619
01:29:32,015 --> 01:29:33,254
(The night deepens as the sweet potatoes cook.)

2620
01:29:33,255 --> 01:29:35,185
When did the time go?

2621
01:29:35,285 --> 01:29:36,285
Right.

2622
01:29:36,555 --> 01:29:38,095
Why are we wearing this again already?

2623
01:29:38,825 --> 01:29:39,855
Hey, that's...

2624
01:29:41,265 --> 01:29:42,325
What's that?

2625
01:29:44,135 --> 01:29:46,235
- Who's that?
- What are you doing?

2626
01:29:46,495 --> 01:29:47,504
What's he doing?

2627
01:29:47,505 --> 01:29:49,034
(The indoor sleeper reappeared.)

2628
01:29:49,035 --> 01:29:50,435
I decided to start jogging.

2629
01:29:50,975 --> 01:29:52,404
(Incredulous)

2630
01:29:52,405 --> 01:29:53,574
I don't believe this.

2631
01:29:53,575 --> 01:29:55,675
Why would you jog at the crack of dawn?

2632
01:29:55,875 --> 01:29:57,575
- I slept alone before.
- Yes.

2633
01:29:57,775 --> 01:29:59,275
It's dead boring...

2634
01:29:59,615 --> 01:30:00,814
and when the others laugh,

2635
01:30:00,815 --> 01:30:02,645
you wonder what they're up to.

2636
01:30:02,815 --> 01:30:04,684
You feel left out.

2637
01:30:04,685 --> 01:30:06,354
- Do you feel anxious?
- You feel guilty.

2638
01:30:06,355 --> 01:30:07,985
- Guilty?
- And antsy.

2639
01:30:08,125 --> 01:30:11,824
If you were to say, "It's fine, come and join us,"

2640
01:30:11,825 --> 01:30:13,725
he'd pretend he doesn't want to but he'd join.

2641
01:30:14,225 --> 01:30:15,051
Joon.

2642
01:30:15,465 --> 01:30:17,095
Come sit down and chat with us.

2643
01:30:18,065 --> 01:30:19,434
- What?
- Have a sweet potato...

2644
01:30:19,435 --> 01:30:20,469
and chat with us.

2645
01:30:20,494 --> 01:30:21,834
You're letting me join?

2646
01:30:21,935 --> 01:30:23,864
- Sure. Come join us.
- Yes.

2647
01:30:23,865 --> 01:30:25,234
- Sit over here.
- Sit down.

2648
01:30:25,235 --> 01:30:27,104
- Sit over here.
- You were right.

2649
01:30:27,105 --> 01:30:29,175
- If I go inside...
- DinDin was right.

2650
01:30:29,205 --> 01:30:31,915
I tried sleeping alone. It's really lonely...

2651
01:30:32,145 --> 01:30:34,084
- and you don't know what to do.
- No.

2652
01:30:34,085 --> 01:30:36,185
It sounds like the rest is having fun.

2653
01:30:36,715 --> 01:30:38,455
Do you want a sweet potato?

2654
01:30:39,055 --> 01:30:40,115
Have one.

2655
01:30:40,785 --> 01:30:43,455
- Here.
- It's good.

2656
01:30:43,925 --> 01:30:46,254
- The black one...
- It's hot. Take it quick!

2657
01:30:46,255 --> 01:30:47,724
- It looks burned.
- You don't want it?

2658
01:30:47,725 --> 01:30:48,725
Peel it by hand.

2659
01:30:48,726 --> 01:30:50,365
That's the trend these days.

2660
01:30:50,835 --> 01:30:52,165
You're all wearing mics.

2661
01:30:52,565 --> 01:30:54,405
- You're not?
- I took mine off long ago.

2662
01:30:54,435 --> 01:30:56,004
- Do you want a mic?
- No.

2663
01:30:56,005 --> 01:30:57,034
(You don't have a mic?)

2664
01:30:57,035 --> 01:30:58,035
Here.

2665
01:30:59,505 --> 01:31:01,044
(He's gifted a charcoal mic.)

2666
01:31:01,045 --> 01:31:02,675
Is this how they look these days?

2667
01:31:03,345 --> 01:31:04,915
- Pretty cool.
- A fiery mic.

2668
01:31:05,245 --> 01:31:07,114
Let's go to sleep. I'm tired.

2669
01:31:07,115 --> 01:31:08,003
I feel sleepy.

2670
01:31:08,645 --> 01:31:10,485
Shall I do the slate thing?

2671
01:31:13,685 --> 01:31:15,725
Here's the manual slate.

2672
01:31:16,055 --> 01:31:17,654
Are you all focused?

2673
01:31:17,655 --> 01:31:20,224
2 Days 1 Night is done for the day.

2674
01:31:20,225 --> 01:31:21,325
One, two, three.

2675
01:31:23,525 --> 01:31:27,735
(Will they survive the Real Winter night?)

2676
01:31:28,435 --> 01:31:32,335
(The temperature drops further as time goes on.)

2677
01:31:33,035 --> 01:31:36,674
(DinDin opens the plastic door...)

2678
01:31:36,675 --> 01:31:39,645
(and struggles to enter the shelter.)

2679
01:31:41,345 --> 01:31:45,554
(He quickly dives into the sleeping bag.)

2680
01:31:45,555 --> 01:31:47,725
(Still, it's cold.)

2681
01:31:48,225 --> 01:31:51,825
(He covers himself from head to toe.)

2682
01:31:52,955 --> 01:31:55,665
(It's freezing cold.)

2683
01:31:55,765 --> 01:31:56,824
Let's go to sleep.

2684
01:31:56,825 --> 01:31:58,294
(It's tough even for experienced Jong Min.)

2685
01:31:58,295 --> 01:31:59,965
Hey. It's so cold.

2686
01:32:00,235 --> 01:32:01,805
It's really so cold.

2687
01:32:02,105 --> 01:32:03,864
- Gosh. My hands...
- How are we going to sleep?

2688
01:32:03,865 --> 01:32:05,205
How are we to sleep out here?

2689
01:32:05,635 --> 01:32:07,475
- Keep your hands inside.
- Okay.

2690
01:32:07,905 --> 01:32:09,575
One thing's for sure.

2691
01:32:10,445 --> 01:32:12,845
We built a better shelter than last year.

2692
01:32:13,275 --> 01:32:14,614
- Right?
- Yes.

2693
01:32:14,615 --> 01:32:15,615
It's well-built.

2694
01:32:15,616 --> 01:32:16,714
It's high and spacious.

2695
01:32:16,715 --> 01:32:18,414
- Yes.
- It's cozy.

2696
01:32:18,415 --> 01:32:20,355
(Their shelter-building skills improved over the year.)

2697
01:32:20,485 --> 01:32:22,724
The weather is abnormally cold,

2698
01:32:22,725 --> 01:32:24,555
- but our shelter's nice.
- Yes, it's nice.

2699
01:32:25,730 --> 01:32:31,300
(They can't help but yawn after the long, hard day.)

2700
01:32:31,995 --> 01:32:33,594
I hope we all survive the night.

2701
01:32:33,595 --> 01:32:34,392
Yes.

2702
01:32:36,435 --> 01:32:39,975
(They drift off to dreamland.)

2703
01:32:40,135 --> 01:32:42,005
(Next episode)

2704
01:32:42,445 --> 01:32:45,975
(The Real Winter trip isn't over yet.)

2705
01:32:46,315 --> 01:32:49,115
(The final journey)

2706
01:32:49,645 --> 01:32:51,084
(The finale)

2707
01:32:51,085 --> 01:32:53,985
(An unavoidable head-on challenge...)

2708
01:32:54,425 --> 01:32:58,025
(where the loser must get his torso wet.)

2709
01:32:58,255 --> 01:33:00,025
(Thrilling)

2710
01:33:00,495 --> 01:33:03,525
(Who will get drenched in the -15°C weather?)

2711
01:33:04,535 --> 01:33:06,594
(After the winter torment...)

2712
01:33:06,595 --> 01:33:08,865
(comes a peaceful trip.)

2713
01:33:09,505 --> 01:33:11,405
(Or so they thought.)

2714
01:33:11,875 --> 01:33:14,675
(Without warning,)

2715
01:33:15,205 --> 01:33:18,475
(they face a string of endless missions.)

2716
01:33:18,815 --> 01:33:21,684
(The arduous itinerary...)

2717
01:33:21,685 --> 01:33:24,015
(is worse than the Real Winter.)

2718
01:33:24,485 --> 01:33:27,585
(A swamp you can't escape)

2719
01:33:27,985 --> 01:33:29,885
(They're losing energy...)

2720
01:33:30,125 --> 01:33:33,855
(while the results remain unchanged.)

2721
01:33:34,365 --> 01:33:37,495
(Can they escape the hellish chain of missions?)

2722
01:33:37,635 --> 01:33:39,634
Who sells ice cream here?

2723
01:33:39,635 --> 01:33:41,735
(See you next week.)
